College Name: M.S. Ramaiah University of Applied Sciences - [MSRUAS]
Info Data: MS Ramaiah University of Applied Sciences (RUAS), Bangalore is committed to work on the philosophy of inclusiveness and service to society and to train its faculty members and students to contribute significantly to the growth of Technology, Science and society through their imaginative, creative and innovative pursuits. University was created by Integrating all the Institutions running under the trust and all Institutions have been converted to the faculties of the University. The university provides various courses at different levels as  in many streams such as Engineering, Design, Science, Commerce, Business Administration, Dental Studies, and Pharmacy courses, etc.

Swami Rama Himalayan University (SRHU), Dehradun offers more than 100+ UG, PG and Doctoral prorams in various disciplines. The flagship courses are B.Tech(CSE), BBA, B.Com (Hons), BCA at UG level and MBA, MCA, M.Tech. M.Sc across multiple streams at PG level. Admission to courses are on the basis of entrance exams such as JEE Main, NEET, MAT, CAT etc. while for most of them, admission is done through the merit of last qualifying exams.

Srinivas University, Mangalore is a Private Research and skill-focused University, established in 2013 by Karnataka State Act. Srinivas University is the flagship of 18 Srinivas Group of Institutions started by A. Shama Rao Foundation, Mangalore, India. Srinivas University offers undergraduate, postgraduate, and research courses under 10 colleges with about 160 courses in the discipline of Engineering, Management, Commerce, Aviation, Nursing Science and many more.

The East West College of Engineering, referred to as EWCE, is part of the East West Group of Institutions. EWCE Bangalore offers 5 courses through Bachelor of Engineering program with an intake of 60 students per branch, admissions for which are accepted through Karnataka Common Entrance Test (KCET).

Global Group of Institutes is a NAAC A+ Accredited Government approved self-financing institute established in 2008 and offers courses like B. Tech, B. Pharm, BBA, BCA, B.Com, B. Sc (MLS, OTT, Radiology, Anesthesia ), HMCT, BTTM,  etc. at UG level, MBA and MCA at PG level along with Diploma courses in  Engineering, and Pharmacy. The institutes are approved by AICTE, PCI, and affiliated with IKG-Punjab Technical University, Jalandhar.

Priyadarshini College of Engineering is one of the premier institutes established in the year 1990. It is affiliated to RTM Nagpur University, Nagpur. The college is approved by AICTE. NAAC has accredited this college with an A+ grade. It offers undergraduate, Post-graduate & Research programs across various disciplines in the field of Engineering & Technology. Admission to these courses is as per the rules of State Common Entrance Cell, Govt. of Maharashtra.

Jeppiaar Institute of Technology Sriperumbudur, Tamil Nadu is a Christian-minority Institution established in 2011. Out of the 506 Engineering Colleges in Tamil Nadu, affiliated to Anna University, Jeppiaar Institute of Technology Sriperumbudur was ranked at 33, according to the Academic Performance Analysis published by the University Examinations 2016.

Seacom Skills University (SSU), Birbhum is a private university established in the year 2014. It is recognized by UGC and approved by AICTE, PCI, and BCI. The University offers various Undergraduate, Postgraduate, and Diploma courses in different disciplines like Engineering, Social Science, Law, Science, Language, Pharmacy, Computer Applications, Agriculture, Commerce, Management, etc. It has state-of-the-art infrastructure and facilities to create a better learning environment.

SRM University Amaravati is a Deemed University that was established in the year 2017. The University is a part of the SRM Group and is situated in Guntur, Andhra Pradesh. The university has collaborated with the University of California Berkeley, MIT USA and EFREI France. SRM University Amaravati is a multi-stream research university that offers degree and research programs in diverse fields like Civil Engineering, Computer Science, Electrical and Electronics, Electronics and Communication, and Mechanical Engineering.

University of Technology, Jaipur is established through State Legislature under Act No 28 of 2017 by the govt of Rajasthan. UOT Jaipur provides 100% placement assistance to students. The highest package offered was worth INR 7.18 lacs per annum. The university offers degree and doctoral programs in the discipline of Engineering, Polytechnic, Pharmacy, Nursing, etc.

CT University is a private university established in 2017. The university is a multi-disciplinary institution that offers under-graduate, post-graduate, and doctoral level programs in Design & Innovation, Humanities & Physical Education, Agriculture & Natural Sciences, Engineering & Technology, Computer Applications, Pharmaceutical, and Healthcare Sciences, Law, Management Studies, Hotel Management, and Airlines & Tourism.

College Name: Malla Reddy College of Engineering for Women - [MRCEW]
Info Data: MRCEW was established on 2008 under the aegis of CES i.e. Chandramma Educational Society. MRCEW offers undergraduate courses in two different streams. The college not only focuses on academics but also focuses on sports life, student life. MRCEW is affiliated to JNTU, Hyderabad and approved by the AICTE, Delhi. MRCEW offers undergraduate course i.e. B.Tech in two different streams. For admission to B.Tech, students are require to appear for the JEE Main entrance exam or TS-EAMCET. In 2018, the Closing rank Cut-off of TS-EAMCET was 92859

Adichunchanagiri University, established in the year 2018, has 6 constituent colleges in Medicine, Pharmacy, Nursing, Engineering, Management, Commerce, and Education. The institute offers various Undergraduate, Postgraduate, and Doctoral programs for which the mode of application is online. The admissions are based on both merit and entrance exams.

Bhabha University is a private university situated in Bhopal, Madhya Pradesh and was established in 2018 by the Ayushmati Education and Social Society. This university is spread across 27 acres of land. The campus of Bhabha University comes with vaious amenities like auditorium and conference facility, smart classrooms, health centre and seminar hall.

Sant Baba Bhag Singh University (SBBSU) was set up in 2015 in Jalandhar, by the SBBS Memorial Charitable Society. It is approved by UGC. SBBSU offers undergraduate, post-graduate, doctorate, and certification courses in the fields of Engineering, Sciences, Humanities, Commerce, Management, Fashion Designing, Hotel Management, Tourism, and Law.

Shivajirao Kadam Institute of Technology & Management (SKITM), Indore is under the aegis of the Transnational Knowledge Society, which was founded in 2009. SKITM is an institution led by academicians, founded by Prof. Shivajirao Kadam, Chancellor of Bharati Vidyapeeth Pune, India’s leading University. SKITM is NAAC Grade ‘A’ accredited & ISO Certified for its high quality of education. Shivajirao Kadam Group of Institutions are affiliated to RGPV, Bhopal & DAVV, Indore, and approved by AICTE, PCI & Department of Higher Education MP.

Rai University (RU) Ahmedabad is a self-financed private University which is situated in Ahmedabad, Gujarat and established by the Gujarat State Legislature under Gujarat Act No. 12 of 2012. The University is approved by the Government of Gujarat as well as the Bar Council of India and also is a member of the Association of Indian Universities. Rai University was awarded as the Best Upcoming Private University in the year 2012 by ASSOCHAM. The current strength of Rai University Ahmedabad is 1,383 including male and female students, as well as a strong and diverse faculty of over 75 members.

Shri Krishna University(SKU), M.P was set up in the year 2018. The university is recognized by the University Grants Commission(UGC) and approved by the Madhya Pradesh government as one of the prominent learning centers. The university offers a number of Integrated, Diploma, and certificate courses along with the full-time degree courses, regulated under NPE.

Anand Institute of Higher Technology, Chennai was established in 2000. It is affiliated to Anna University, Chennai, and all the courses at AIHT are approved by AICTE. AIHT is a sister university of Kalasalingam University.

Arunai Engineering College (AEC) is a private institute established in 1993 at Tiruvannamalai, Tamil Nadu. It is approved by AICTE and is affiliated to Anna University, Chennai. The college offers B.E, B.Tech at the undergraduate level and ME, M.Tech, MBA at the postgraduate level. It has top-class infrastructural facilities and provides financial assistance to students. More than 4500 students are placed in reputed companies.

Bharati Vidyapeeth College of Engineering is situated in Kolhapur in the Maharashtra state of India. The college offers 6 courses across 1 stream namely Engineering and 2 degrees like B.Tech and M.Tech. Admission to the college is made on the basis of entrance exams conducted such as MHT CET and JEE Main. The application process for the admission is online. Graduates from the college are placed in Infosys, same corner, TCS, Just Dial, Saankhya Labs, Qspiders, Kirloskar brothers, Amazon, etc. with an average salary package of IRN 1.86 LPA and highest salary package of INR 4.5 LPA.

DMI College of Engineering was established in the year 2001 and is located in Chennai, Tamilnadu, India. The college has a campus of 55 acres of land. It is affiliated to Anna University, Chennai. The college is accredited by NBA and approved by AICTE.

College Name: Dayananda Sagar Academy of Technology and Management - [DSATM]
Info Data: Dayananda Sagar Academy of Technology and Management, Bangalore offers 5 undergraduate as well as 1 postgraduate course. The institute was established in the year 2011 in a vast area of 10 acres. The whole campus is Wi-Fi enabled to ensure internet availability to the students. The institute is affiliated to Visvesvaraya Technological University, approved by AICTE and accredited by NBA. The basic eligibility criteria for UG courses are passing 10+2 and for PG programs, it is a graduation degree from any stream. The admission is based on entrance examinations such as COMEDK UGET, , PGCET, and CAT/XAT/MAT. The college is approved by the NBA, AICTE, UGC, and is ranked 126th in NIRF 2020 for Engineering colleges.

Dhole Patil College of Engineering (DPCOE) established in 2008, is a premier Engineering and Management College located in Pune, Maharashtra. DPCOE offers an undergraduate degree in BE in 6 specializations, and an MBA degree in 5 specializations. It is the first college in Pune to offer an undergraduate engineering degree in Automobile Engineering. The admission in DPCOE is strictly based on the merit secured in either the state level or national level entrance examinations. DPCOE has also received the Rotary Professional Excellence Award for the Best Urban College in Education.

Don Bosco Institute of Technology (DBIT), Bangalore is a premier institute established in the year 2001. The institute is affiliated to Visvesvaraya Technological University (VTU), Belagavi and accredited by NAAC B+ grade. Don Bosco Institute of Technology offers undergraduate and postgraduate program that are recognised by All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE), New Delhi. DBIT offers BE in several specializations. NBA has accredited the courses like BE Computer Science & Engineering, Electronics and Communication Engineering, Information Science & Engineering, Electrical and Electronics Engineering and Civil Engineering. Admission to BE course is based on marks secured in 10+2 and a valid score in CET/ COMEDK Exams. DBIT also offers MBA an a postgraduate course. Admission to MBA is based on graduation marks and a valid score in entrance exams like PGCET/ GMAT/ KMAT/ CAT/ / / MAT/ / XAT/ NMAT etc.

Dronacharya Group of Institutions, Greater Noida (DGI) is a private institute established in the year 2006 by Smt. Anguri Devi Charitable Trust. The Dronacharya Group of Institutions, Greater Noida is affiliated with Dr. A. P. J. Abdul Kalam Technical University (AKTU), Lucknow and the institute is approved by the All- India Council for Technical Education (AICTE).

Gandhinagar Institute of Technology was established in the year 2006 by Platinum Foundation Trust. It is a private institute situated near village “Moti Bhoyan” on Gandhi Nagar, Gujarat and 24 km away from Ahmedabad city. The institute is approved by All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE) and affiliated to Gujarat Technological University. It provides B.E, M.E and MBA in different fields. Admission to same through GUJCET/ PGCET/ CAT/ MAT/ XAT score.

HMR Institute of Technology and Management (HMRITM), Delhi is a prestigious institute established in the year 2002. It is affiliated with Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University and has been approved by AICTE. GGSIPU conducts the Common Entrance Test (CET), which serves as the basis for admission to all courses. The intake for PG courses is 60 seats, whereas the intake for B.Tech degrees varies by branch, ranging from 60 to 180. The institute offers B.Tech and B.Tech Lateral Entry programs at the UG level and MBA at the PG level through nine departments.

College Name: Indore Institute of Science and Technology - [IIST]
Info Data: Indore Institute of Science and Technology (IIST), Indore is a prestigious institute established in the year 2003. It is affiliated to Rajiv Gandhi Proudyogiki Vishwavidyalaya, Bhopal & is recognized by UCG and DTE, Madhya Pradesh Govt. Accredited A+ grade by NAAC, IIST Indore offers 10+ programs and 9 branches under the UG and PG programs that include BTech and ME courses. The institute offers a 4-year long BTech program across several disciplines at the undergraduate level. Admission to this course is primarily based on the JEE Mains score followed by DTE MP counselling. For the year 2023, the IIST Indore JEE Mains cutoff ranged from 450013 rank to 1105143 rank for the general category candidates. Along with this, the institute offers an ME program at the PG level for a duration of 2 years. This course is offered under 3 different specialisations. IIST Indore accepts GATE scores for allowing admission to its ME program.

The K.S Rangasamy College of Engineering, established in 1994 is located in Tiruchengode, Tamil Nadu. The college offers 2 courses at the undergraduate level, ie. B.Tech and BE with 6 specializations, and 4 courses at the postgraduate level namely, ME, MCA, M. Tech with 6 specializations, and MBA. Selection to the undergraduate courses happens based on scores obtained in TNEA, and selection for the postgraduate courses is done based on scores in TANCET and GATE and for MBA based on TANCET. The application for these courses is available online.

Loyola Institute of Technology was established in 2003, at Chennai, Tamil Nadu. The institute has the approval of AICTE & is affiliated to Anna University. LIT Chennai offers BE program at the undergraduate level and ME, MCA, MBA programs at the post-graduate level. Candidates can register for the courses online through the official website. The institute has also maintained a great placement record over the years.

Lucknow Institute of Technology is a private institute present in the technology capital of Uttar Pradesh, Kanpur. It is a lavish green campus with unparalleled infrastructure and excellence in education. It is affiliated with Dr. A. P. J. Abdul Kalam Technical University, Lucknow, and the Board of Technical Education, UP. It also has approval from AICTE. Check Lucknow Institute of Technology, Lucknow, Uttar Pradesh Admission

Madha Engineering College is located at Kundrathur in Chennai. It was established in 1998. The College belongs to the Madha Group of Educational Trust and is affiliated to Anna University, approved by AICTE. The college offers UG and PG degree courses in various specializations of the engineering field. Madha Engineering College offers B.E. Course across 7 fields and B.Tech courses in 2 fields for the duration of 4 years at the undergraduate level. The college provides M.E. courses in 5 specializations with MCA and MBA courses for the duration of 2 years. The courses offered by this college are affiliated to Anna University and are approved by the University Grant commission.

College Name: Maharaj Vijayaram Gajapathi Raj College of Engineering - [MVGRCE]
Info Data: Maharaj Vijayaram Gajapathi Raj College of Engineering (MVGRCE) is an affiliation of Jawaharlal Nehru Technical University, Kakinada. It is ranked at 76th position among Top 100 private Engineering Institute by i3RC Times Rankings in 2018. The college offers B.Tech, MBA, and M.Tech to its applicants for Undergraduate and Postgraduate admissions respectively. In addition, it also offers some Ph.D. programs in MECH, ECE, CSE, CHEM, CIV. The placement rate of MVGRCE is 70% with 28 LPA as the highest CTC and 5 LPA as the average CTC offered to students by companies like Amazon, Mu- Sigma, Jaro Education, Hansa Solutions, Riktam Technology, Effftronics, Nine Leaps, etc.

Manav Rachna University (MRU), Faridabad is ranked 174th (Engineering) and ranked 151-200 (University) by NIRF India Rankings 2020 by MHRD. MRU Faridabad provides 100% placement assistance to students. More than 100 companies participated in the placement drive at the university and offered various roles to the students with great salary packages. The highest annual salary package offered amounts to INR 23 LPA. MRU Faridabad offers various UG & PG Courses in the discipline of Engineering & Technology, Law, Education, Business Studies and Applied Sciences.

Established in 1986, Orissa Engineering College is the first private engineering college of Odisha. Counted amongst the best technical institutes of the country, the institute is AICTE approved and NBA and NAAC accredited.

R.D. Engineering College (RDEC) is an engineering college, located in the city of Ghaziabad in the state of Uttar Pradesh. R.D. Engineering College is one of the pioneering institutions founded by the Rameshwar Dayal Educational Trust. The Rajeshwar Dayal Educational Trust was established on April 20, 2004, to provide high-quality education, encourage creative talent, and establish an epicenter of excellence in learning and research. The institute was founded as a self-supporting institution.

College Name: Sri Indu Institute of Engineering & Technology - [SIIET]
Info Data: Sri Indu Institute of Engineering and Technology (SIIET), Hyderabad is a private college established in 2006, affiliated to JNTUH and approved by AICTE. The college offers undergraduate and diploma courses in the discipline of Engineering and Technology across 7 specializations. Admission to the SIIET is done on the basis of the performance of the candidates in the state level entrance exam.

Rajalakshmi Institute of Technology (RIT), Chennai is a private engineering college established in 2008, affiliated to Anna University and approved by All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE). It offers undergraduate courses in the discipline of Engineering and Technology. Additionally, the institute has placed more than 1100 students and invited 275+ recruiters. The highest package offered at INR 12 LPA. Some of the top recruiters are Infosys, Justdial, L & T InfoTech, Wipro, JBM Auto Systems, Amazon, Capgemini, Altair etc.

College Name: Rajasthan Institute of Engineering and Technology - [RIET]
Info Data: Rajasthan Institute of Engineering and Technology (RIET), Jaipur, is a premier technical & management institution, which was established in the year 2000 by a prominent group of Educationists and Philanthropists, Chandrawati Education Society, with a vision of establishing a World Class Education and Training Institute that creates a vibrant community of Intellectuals and Entrepreneurs by generating creativity, competence and commitment in their character to ensure sustainable development of society. The institution is approved by All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE) New Delhi and it is duly affiliated with . The institute offers many specializations of engineering disciplines at  with MCA and MBA Courses altogether as a part of the curriculum.

College Name: Rajshree Institute of Management and Technology - [RIMT]
Info Data: RIMT (Rajshree Institute of Management and Technology), Bareilly was established in 2009. The institute offers UG, PG and Diploma programs in various specializations such as Engineering, Management, and Science. Admission to RIMT is done on the basis of entrance tests. The admission forms are available at the city office and college campus of the institute. The B.Tech, MBA and M.Tech program is affiliated to AKTU, Lucknow whereas PG diploma and Polytechnic program is affiliated to BTE, Lucknow. B.Sc, BBA, B.Com, B.Ed is affiliated to MJPRU.

SSM College of Engineering is situated in the city of Namakkal in Tamil Nadu state. It was established in the year of 1998 under the approval of All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE). The college was established by the ‘Gnanathandhai’ SSM Subramaniam and is headed by the Chairman ‘Cavalier’ Dr. M. S. Mathivaanan. SSMCE is affiliated to Anna University, Chennai. SSMCE Namakkal has acquired 8th place in the rankings for the Anna University Engineering Colleges.

College Name: Sam College of Engineering and Technology - [SAMCET]
Info Data: SAM College of Engineering and Technology (SAMCET) was established in the year 2007. The institute is approved by the All India Council of Technical Education (AICTE) and Government of India, New Delhi. SAMCET is affiliated to Barkatullah University, Bhopal, Madhya Pradesh Board of Secondary Education, Bhopal and Makhanlal Chaturvedi Rashtriya Patrakarita Avam Sanchar Vishwavidhyalaya, Bhopal. The institute offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses in Management and Engineering.

College Name: Sanghvi Institute of Management and Science - [SIMS]
Info Data: Sanghvi Institute of Management and Science, Indore was established in 2006. The institute is a Private College of Indore located in the state of India Madhya Pradesh. The institute is one of the prestigious institutes and is accredited from AICTE, DTE, and is associated with Devi Ahilya Vishwavidyalaya. The institute offers more than 28 courses in various branches such as IT, Engineering, Science, Management, Commerce and Banking. The institute grants specializations in different courses such as B.Tech, B.Com, B.Sc, B.B.A, BCA.

College Name: Sarvajanik College of Engineering and Technology - [SCET]
Info Data: The Sarvajanik College of Engineering and Technology was established at Surat in 1995. According to IndiaToday, the college was ranked as the 17th for the year 2018 in Gujarat. College offers various Undergraduate and Postgraduate courses in the field of Technology and Computer Applications. Major IT companies coming for placement are Thomson Reuters CMC Ltd., Collebra, BlazeCLan, to name a few. Admissions are based on the GUJCET merit rank.

Seacom Engineering College was established in 2006 in Howrah to impart higher education to the students in fields like Engineering, Management, and Computer Applications. The college offers Undergraduate courses like B.Tech or B.E in subjects like IT, Electronics and Computer Engineering, Civil engineering, Mechanical engineering, Marine Engineering, and Computer Science and Engineering. The college also offers postgraduate courses like MCA and MBA. The undergraduate students are shortlisted based on their Entrance Test JEE and WBJEE results. The students for M.C.A are shortlisted completely on merit-basis and the selection of MBA students is done based on their Entrance test named CAT or MAT results.

College Name: Seth Jai Parkash Mukand Lal Institute of Engineering and Technology - [JMIT]
Info Data: Seth Jai Parkash Mukand Lal Institute of Engineering & Technology [JMIT], Yamuna Nagar was established in 1995 and duly affiliated to Kurukshetra University. JMIT is a chain of twenty-two institutions spread over Haryana, U.P, and Punjab and owe their existence to the munificent and philanthropic spirit of Seth Mukand Lal, a close adherent of Gandhi Ji. He came under the Gandhian influence in earlier twenties. Gandhi Ji had fondly nicknamed him "Pagle Bhagat". Seth Mukand Lal reportedly bore the entire expenditure incurred in the holding of All India Congress Sessions on the banks of river Ravi, Lahore in 1929 where a resolution for complete independence of India was adopted.

College Name: Shah and Anchor Kutchhi Engineering College - [SAKEC]
Info Data: Shah and Anchor Kutchhi Engineering College [SAKEC], was established in the year 1985. The college is managed by Mahavir Education Trust, affiliated to the University of Mumbai, approved by D.T.E. and AICTE. It ranked 251-300 in NIRF 2020. Awarded “A” Grade by NAAC. The college offers undergraduate B.Tech. courses in Computer Engineering, Information Technology, Electronics and Computer Science and Electronics & Telecommunication Engineering, Artificial Intelligence and Data Science, Cyber Security, Electronics Engineering (VLSI Design Technology), Electronics and Communication (Advance Communication Technology). It also offers Post Graduate Course M.Tech. in . The U.G. Program in Computer Engineering and Information Technology of the college has been awarded accreditation by the National Board of Accreditation (NBA) for 3 Years.

College Name: Sri Indu College of Engineering and Technology - [SICET] Ibrahimpatnam
Info Data: Sri Indu College of Engineering and Technology, Hyderabad established in 2001, is affiliated to JNTUH, Hyderabad and approved by AICTE. The college offers UG and PG courses in the discipline of Engineering & Technology and Management across various specializations, approved by UGC.

Sri Krishna Institute of Technology (SKIT), Bangalore is a private engineering college established in the year 2001. The institute has been approved by AICTE and is affiliated to Visvesvaraya Technological University. It offers B.E across six disciplines viz. Civil Engineering, Computer Science and Engineering, Information Science & Engineering, Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning, Mechanical Engineering and Electronics and Communication Engineering. Admission to SKIT Bangalore is based on JEE Main/CET/COMEDK score.

Sriram Engineering College (SEC) is a private engineering institute established in 1993. It is located in the Thiruvallur district of Tamil Nadu. The college has been approved by AICTE & is affiliated to Anna University. It offers B.E. & B.Tech at the UG level and M.Tech at the PG level. The college aims at providing quality technical education and excellent placement opportunities to its students.

College Name: St. Thomas College of Engineering and Technology- [STC]
Info Data: St Thomas College of Engineering and Technology (STCET), Alappuzha was established in 2010 and managed by St. Thomas Educational Society; Adoor.STCET shall be a lead institution in Engineering having national eminence and international visibility.

College Name: Swami Vivekananda Institute of Science and Technology - [SVIST]
Info Data: Swami Vivekananda Institute of Science and Technology - [SVIST], Kolkata, West Bengal was established in 2008 and is affiliated to Maulana Abul Kalam Azad University of Technology. The college offers undergraduate courses for B. Tech in various disciplines. The college also offers a two years master degree program for MBA and 3 years Polytechnic diploma under two specializations.

Techno International New Town (TINT) is a private institute under the aegis of Techno India Group. Established in 2005, it is a prestigious institute set up in Newtown, Rajarhat, Kolkata. It is affiliated to Maulana Abul Kalam Azad University of Technology and has been approved by AICTE. The institute is also ranked at the 13th position among the top 15 engineering institutes in the Eastern Region in Times of India Engineering Rankings 2024.

Established in 2009, Theem College of Engineering, Palghar has been since managed by Haji Jamaluddin Thim Trust. TCOE Palghar courses include BE and Polytechnic. Admission is provided on the basis of composite score i.e., marks obtained after adding 50% of MHT-CET/ JEE Main marks and 50% of normalized standard Higher Secondary Examination in Physics, Chemistry, and Mathematics or its equivalent examination marks. However, the candidates are eligible only if they have completed the Higher Secondary School Examination of Maharashtra State Board of Secondary & Higher Education or its equivalent.

Xavier Institute of Engineering is a private institute established in the year 2005. It is AICTE approved, affiliated to University of Mumbai and has got recognition by the Directorate of Technical Education, Govt. of Maharashtra It is a Christian minority college which offers only UG Engineering degree in three specialisations and takes admission through entrance tests.

Velammal Institute of Technology, Tamil Nadu is a premier private educational institution that was established in 2008. The Institute is affiliated with Anna University and is approved by the AICTE and NBA. The Institute has also been accredited by NAAC.

Established in 2002, Vignan's Institute of Information Technology (VIIT) is a private institute offering UG, PG and Diploma courses in the discipline of Engineering & Technology across various specializations. The institute is affiliated with Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University, Kakinada and it is approved by AICTE, UGC, and NBA.

Knowledge Institute of Technology (KIOT), Salem is awarded ‘Best Upcoming Engineering College’ in Tamil Nadu in Sustainable Institute Industry Partnership Award by Society for Educational and Entrepreneurship Development (SEED) and ‘Best Performing Institution for Innovation of Engineering & Technology IET’ by Recruitment Analysis Council. The institute has a record of providing more than 90% placement every year and international placement with a salary package worth INR 18.5 lakhs per annum.

Vasireddy Venkatadri Institute Of Technology (VVIT), a premier Private (Autonomous) College of Andhra Pradesh which was established in 2007 under Social Educational Trust by Sri. Vasireddy Vidya Sagar to provide world-class technical education to conquer tomorrow's technology at the global level with human values. It is situated in Nambur village, Pedakakani Mandal of Guntur district, Andhra Pradesh. It offers undergraduate and postgraduate Engineering courses and MCA. VVIT has emerged as one of the top ten Engineering Colleges from the 200 engineering colleges affiliated to  and accredited to NAAC by ‘A’ grade. Its  are accredited by NBA.

Sushant University – Erstwhile Ansal University, Gurgaon is ranked 4th for Best Emerging Business School by Times of India B-School Survey and ranked 1st for Private Architecture School by Outlook. More than 250 recruiters have visited for on-campus recruitment. The institute has a strong 3500+ alumni network and over 500 students have gone studying abroad under SU’s partnership program with universities in the United States, UK and Australia.
William Carey University was established in 2005 in Shillong. The University currently has 11 departments and offers 107 courses.

Career Point University (CPU), Rajasthan was established in 2012. The 50 Acre campus was established by Rajasthan State Legislature Council under ‘Career Point University Act’. The University offers Undergraduate, Postgraduate and Diploma programs approved by AICTE in streams like Management, Law, Technology, Computer, Science, and Social work. CPU is also approved by University Grants Commission (UGC), PCI, BAR council, and NCTE. Admission to the courses is done on the basis of various national-level examinations such as JEE Main, , or CAT.

SRM Ghaziabad is a renowned educational institution that aspires to be one of the best private universities in Delhi-NCR. SRM Ghaziabad was established in the year 1997. The university is recognized as Category 1 & A Grade by UGC & MHRD and is approved by AICTE & PCI. SRM Ghaziabad offers various UG, PG & Doctoral Programs. It also offers professional degree courses in Engineering and Technology, Management, Computer Applications, Pharmacy, and Hotel Management.

College Name: Chhotubhai Gopalbhai Patel Institute of Technology, Uka Tarsadia University - [CGPIT]
Info Data: Chhotubhai Gopalbhai Patel Institute of Technology (CGPIT) is a self-financed institution started in 2009 by Bardoli Pradesh Kelavani Mandal (BPKM). The college is affiliated to a state private university named UKA Tarsadia University. The college is located in the Malibu campus of the university.

College Name: K.S. School of Engineering and Management- [KSSEM]
Info Data: KSSEM Bangalore (K.S School of Engineering and Management) was established in the year 2010 in Bangalore, Karnataka. The institute is affiliated with Visvesvaraya Technological University, Belgaum, and approved by the All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE). KSSEM is currently offering three courses in the field of Engineering and Management. At the UG level, the institute offers a B.E., and for the PG level, the institute has M.Tech and MBA degrees to offer.

Vivekananda Institute of Technology (VIT), Jaipur is a private engineering college established in the year 2008. It is affiliated to Rajasthan Technical University and is approved by AICTE. Presently, it is running a B.Tech. the program across 5 specializations. It also offers lateral entry to the course. Admission to the VIT Jaipur is done on the basis of JEE Main and REAP Counselling. The institute has excellent infrastructural facilities and a good placement record. In the year 2019, VIT has placed more than 2515 students with the highest package of INR 10 LPA and the average package of INR 2.5 LPA. The highest international package is recorded at INR 53 LPA. Some of the top recruiters include Wipro, Microsoft, HDFC, Intel, Amazon, Accenture, Oppo, etc.

PERI Institute of Technology strives to offer quality-based education to students of different cultures by way of career education programs. The Insitute is affiliated to Anna University and has been approved by AICTE. It lays great emphasis on offering an education that is intellectually challenging and one that reflects a high standard of performance. The college is completely dedicated to serving a culturally and ethnically diverse population. It operates with the mission of providing requirement-based education in a stimulating and challenging study environment. PERI Institute provides state-of-the-art infrastructure facilities to achieve excellence in teaching-learning, Research and Development.

College Name: Vidya Pratishthan's Kamalnayan Bajaj Institute of Engineering and Technology - [VPKBIET] Baramati
Info Data: Vidya Pratishthan's Kamalnayan Bajaj Institute of Engineering and Technology (VPKBIET) is located in Baramati, Pune, Maharashtra. The institute offers BE program in six specializations, while it offers five specializations in the ME program. The admission to these courses is based on the merit secured in the entrance examination and is regulated through the guidelines issued by the Directorate of Technical Education(DTE), Maharashtra. The entrance exams accepted for the admission are MHCET and GATE. Candidates need to apply online for the admission process through the official website.

Adhiparasakthi College of Engineering Arcot (APCE), established in 1984, is an affiliation of Anna University, Chennai. The institute offers 2 Undergraduate and 3 Postgraduate programs in various specializations. Admission to UG programs is based on the TNEA exam and admission to the PG programs is based on the TANCET exam. The eligibility criteria for the UG programs is 50% marks in the 10+2 in science stream and the eligibility criteria for the PG programs is Graduate degree in relevant stream. Interested candidates are applicable to apply online as well as offline for the admission process.

College Name: SRM Institute of Science and Technology Ramapuram Campus
Info Data: SRM Institute of Science and Technology (SRM IST) Ramapuram Campus, formerly known as SRM University was established in 2004. It is located in Ramapuram, Chennai, Tamil Nadu. SRM Ramapuram has been approved by UGC and AICTE. SRM Ramapuram has been accredited by NAAC with the highest grade of A++. SRM Ramapuram provides various undergraduate, postgraduate and doctoral programs in Engineering, Science and Humanities, Management and Dental.

College Name: St. Andrews Institute of Technology and Management - [SAITM]
Info Data: St. Andrews Institute of Technology and Management (SAITM), Gurgaon is awarded ‘Best Engineering College for promoting Industry-Academic Interface’ by the Hon’ble Government of Goa Smt. Mridula Sinha. SAITM Gurgaon offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses in the discipline of Engineering, Management and Computer Application. Admission is done on the basis of merit and entrance examinations. The institute provides 100% placement assistance to its students. The highest package is recorded at INR 40 LPA and the average package is recorded at INR 8 LPA. Some of the potential employers include

Shri Ramswaroop Memorial (SRM), Institute of Technology was founded in Lucknow, Uttar Pradesh, in 2012. The institution is an affiliate of Lucknow's Shri Ramswaroop Memorial University (SRMU) and is approved by the AICTE. The engineering stream is covered by a number of UG and PG programmes at the SRM Institute of Technology Lucknow.

JNTUK University College of Engineering Vizianagaram was founded in 2007, approved by the All India Council for Technical Education. Being a constituent college of Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University Kakinada, the institute has a highly polished educational infrastructure with an international outlook and live synergy with the relevant industries. The college aims at rendering human resources to the industry in the disciplines of Computer Science and Information Technology, Infrastructure development, Communication, networking and more.

St. Joseph's Institute of Technology is a higher education institution in Chennai, India offering UG and PG courses such as BE/ BTech, and ME. in various specializations. The courses are offered to students to fulfill the eligibility criteria of both merit and entrance based process. Admissions at the college are mostly merit-based. The interested students may visit the campus for the registration to apply for the admission.

Ramco Institute of Technology, situated in the city of Rajapalayam, Tamil Nadu was established in the year 2013. RIT is affiliated to Anna University, Chennai. The institute is also approved by AICTE. It offers a Bachelor of Engineering program across 5 specializations. The aim is to provide high-quality technical education and create skilled Engineers and Technologists who are capable of working in an integrated environment.

ITM Vocational University (ITMVU), established in 2014 is a private university located in Vadodara, Gujarat. The university is approved by UGC and AICTE and is best know for its wide range of vocational courses. ITMVU offers various undergraduate and postgraduate courses in the field of Engineering, Management, Science and Computer Application.

College Name: Greater Noida Institute of Technology, IPU - [GNIT]
Info Data: Greater Noida Institute of Technology or GNIT, Greater Noida is one of the reputed private engineering colleges in India. The college is approved by the All India Council of Technical Education (AICTE) and is affiliated with Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam Technical University, Lucknow. GNIT, Greater Noida is part of the GNIOT Group of Institutions and offers various undergraduate and postgraduate courses in engineering, management, commerce, and paramedical sciences.

Netaji Subhas University (NSU) Jamshedpur formerly known as Netaji Subash Institute of Business Management (NSIBM) is the first approved private university of Jamshedpur, established to provide world-class education amenities to the students. The university was established in the year 2018, approved by University Grants Commission(UGC), AICTE, NCTE, BCI, INC, JNRC and PCI. NSU was. The university provides students with a highly qualified team of faculty memvers who are experienced and professional in their fields.

College Name: Greater Noida Institute of Technology (Engineering Institute)
Info Data: Greater Noida Institute of Technology, Greater Noida is one of the most reputed private Engineering and Management institutes in North India. It has been ranked 143rd for MBA by The Week 2020. The Institute is awarded the Best Management Institute award in North India for Industry Interface by Rashtriya Shiksha Gaurav Puraskar Ceremony – 2019. GNIOT (Engineering Institute) has achieved NAAC A+ grade in its first cycle.

Arunodaya University, Arunachal Pradesh was established by The State Legislature and is approved under the UGC Act 1956 vested in 2014, with programs for Degrees, Diplomas, and Certificates ranging from Under graduation, Bachelor’s, Post-graduation, Ph.D., and M.Phil. The Institution has been established to provide the growing needs of higher education in the country.

Shri Guru Ram Rai University (SGRRU), Dehradun is specialized in 103 courses of 10 streams. Graduates from the university are placed in companies such as Accenture, Apex Pharma, Axis Bank, Bajaj Capital, DA Milano, Deloitte, Genpact, etc. SGRRU offers UG, PG, Diploma, Doctoral, and Certificate courses in the fields of Arts, Science, Commerce, Medical, Management, Agriculture. Recently, the college is also offering B.Sc in agriculture that is ICAR approved. Admission to the same is merit-based.

Jagadguru Sri Shivarathreeshwara Academy of Technical Education which is also known as JSS Academy of Technical Education (JSSATE) is an engineering college situated in the city of Bangalore. JSSATE was established in the year of 1997 beneath the JSS Mahavidyapeetha which is located at Mysore. JSSATE is affiliated by VTU (i.e.) Visvesvaraya Technological University in Belgaum, Karnataka, India. It has been ranked by NIRF at 55 among the top universities in India in 2019.

College Name: SDM College of Engineering and Technology - [SDMCET]
Info Data: SDM College of Engineering and Technology (SDMCET), Dharwad was started by SDME Society in 1979. It is a Self Financed Autonomous educational Institute. It is affiliated to Visvesvaraya Technical University (Belgaum) & University Grants Commission (New Delhi). The Institute has been conferred twice by the National Board of Accreditation & selected for Technical Education Quality Improvement Program (TEQIP).

Jagdishprasad Jhabarmal Tibrewala University (JJTU) is a private university in Jhunjhunu, India. The institute was established in the year 2009 & is recognized by UGC, New Delhi. It offers multiple UG, PG, Diploma, PG Diploma, Doctoral, and certificate courses in various specializations like Arts, Science, Commerce, Management, Engineering, Library Science, Law, Nursing, Pharmacy, architecture, etc.

Jawaharlal Nehru Engineering College (JNEC) is listed at 5 among Top 10 private Engineering Colleges in India by AISEET 2019. JNEC Aurangabad is well-known for its B.E. (CSE) as it provides a good placement to its students. As per the recent placements of 2019, top reputed companies like Pin Click, Wipro Elite, Byju’s and TATA Consultancy Services Ltd. offered a salary package of INR 6 LPA to many CSE students.

Mohamed Sathak Engineering College (MSEC) is established in the state of Tamil Nadu in 1984. The College is affiliated to Anna University. The College offers various undergraduate and postgraduate courses.

AVS Engineering College (AVSEC) is one of the most premium institutes located in the Steel City Salem, Tamil Nadu, and was established in 2008. The college is situated well within the town limit of Salem city and located at Ammapet, Salem-3. The college is 2 km away from Salem Town Railway Station and 7 km away from Salem Junction. It is renowned for imparting quality education to future engineers and managers. It is recognized under 2(f) of the UGC Act 1956. It is approved by AICTE and is affiliated with Anna University.

Ahmedabad Institute of Technology is a premier institution located in Gota, Ahmedabad. It is approved by All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE). Ahmedabad Institute of Technology was placed in the 32nd position among the top 100 engineering colleges in India in 2019 by Outlook India. Ahmedabad Institute of Technology offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses. The admission to this college is done through online mode. Students can take admission by sitting for relevant entrance examinations. Placement opportunities are pretty decent in this institution, with a number of renowned companies like Coca Cola, ICICI Prudential Life Insurance, Ratnamani Metals and Tubes, John Energy Ltd., and eClinicalWorks.

College Name: Amritsar College of Engineering and Technology - [ACET]
Info Data: Amritsar College of Engineering and Technology is an autonomous College and one of the top engineering institutes in the Punjab Region. The College is affiliated with Punjab Technical University, Kapurthala. ACET Is accredited with grade A by the National Assessment and Accreditation Council and by NBA.

Anand International College of Engineering (Anand ICE), Jaipur is awarded ‘Grade A’ Engineering college in Rajasthan by RTU, Kota and ranked 5th among the 'Top Emerging Private Institutes Of India' by the Times of India. The institute has an average record of 100% placement for the last 3 years. The highest salary package offered amounts to INR 12 LPA. AICE Jaipur offers an undergraduate course in the discipline of Civil Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Electrical Engineering, etc.

College Name: M H Saboo Siddik College of Engineering - [MHSSCOE]
Info Data: Mohammad Haji Sabo Siddik College of Engineering (MHSSCOE) is a well-known technical institute established in 1984 at Mumbai, Maharashtra. It is approved by AICTE and is affiliated to the University of Mumbai. The college offers Bachelor of Engineering programs across 7 specializations. Admission to the program is granted based on MHT-CET or JEE Mains score. Students under different branches of engineering get placed in reputed companies every year.

Aurangabad College of Engineering (ACE) is a private engineering institute established in 2010. It is approved by AICTE and is affiliated to Babasaheb Bhimrao Ambedkar Marathwada University. Presently, it is running a Bachelor of technology program across five disciplines. The institute provides excellent technical education under highly qualified faculties.

College Name: Drs. Kiran and Pallavi Patel Global University
Info Data: Drs. Kiran and Pallavi Patel Global University (KPGU), Vadodara was established in 2004 and is approved by AICTE, PCI, NBA and UGC. The university offers various undergraduate, postgraduate and diploma courses in the disciplines of Engineering & Technology, Management, Science, Pharmacy, Nursing, and Ayurvedic Medicine. Admission to KGPU depends on the performance of the candidates in state/ national level entrance exams. Furthermore, the university has highly qualified and well experienced faculty members. As well as, the university has a dedicated Training and Placement Cell which provides 100% placement assistance to its students.

Cambridge Institute of Technology was founded in the year 2001 at Tatisilwai, a place 16 km away from Ranchi, the capital of Jharkhand. The institute was started under the guidance of late Dr Bahadur Singh – A Social Reformer and Educationist and was promoted by the Cambridge Trust of India (Registered under Indian Trust Act). Cambridge Institute of Technology is affiliated to Ranchi University, Ranchi and Government of Jharkhand.

College Name: Coimbatore Institute of Engineering and Technology - [CIET]
Info Data: Coimbatore Institute of Engineering and Technology (CIET) was established in 2001 under the aegis of Kovai Kalaimagai Education trust. It is private self-financing engineering college affiliated to Anna University. CIET is approved by AICTE and accredited by NAAC with ‘A’ grade. It works with an aim to provide quality education with the best infrastructure. The institute offers seven undergraduate and seven postgraduate Engineering and Management courses.

The College of Engineering Thalassery, established in 2000, is affiliated to APJ Abdul Kalam Technological University (KTU). It offers undergraduate and postgraduate programmes in engineering. The admission procedure is conducted via entrance tests as well as on the basis of merit. Placement opportunities are abundant, with many recruiters visiting the institution in order to hire eligible candidates. The college has Hostel, transportation, labs, seminar halls, and various other amenities.

College Name: D. Y. Patil College of Engineering
Info Data: D. Y. Patil College of Engineering was established in the year 1984 and is affiliated to SavitriBai Phule Pune University. The College is recognized by DTE and approved by AICTE. It is also accredited Grade A by NAAC.

College Name: Dr. Sudhir Chandra Sur Institute of Technology & Sports Complex - [SURTECH]
Info Data: Dr. Sudhir Chandra Sur Institute of Technology and Sports Complex (SURTECH), established in 2009, is one of the leading Engineering College in Kolkata as well as in Eastern India, located centrally in Dum Dum on a land area of 5.64 acres. The institute is ranked 5th best private college by India Today in 2023. It is affiliated to WBSCTVESD & MAKAUT and the only institute with its own sports complex in Kolkata. It is one of the flagship Institution under the aegis of JIS Group Educational Initiative. The Campus of the Institutions is green pollution-free exquisitely landscaped and its infrastructure includes Wi-Fi enabled Campus, Language labs, Sports ground, Hostels, etc.

East Point Group of Institutions (EPGI), Bangalore is a group of private institutions and is affiliated with Visvesvaraya Technological University.  The Institute was founded in 1997 and is managed by M.G Charitable Trust. East Point Group of Institutions ranked 40th in Top Private Engineering Institutes and 43rd in Top Engineering Institutes by Times of India, 2024.

GITA Autonomous College, Bhubaneswar is ranked 1 among Private Engineering College in Odisha by Times of India and ranked 5 among Top Engineering College in India by Times Engineering Survey. The institute is a part of the famous Vidya Bharati Educational Trust. Accredited by National Assessment of Accreditation Council, GITA offers degree courses in the discipline of Engineering, Business Administration, Computer Application, etc.

Global Institute of Technology (GIT) situated in Jaipur has ranked consistently among the top 5 Engineering colleges in Rajasthan and it was set up in the year 2002. The institute imparts the best education and knowledge in the field of Engineering & Technology. It is affiliated to Rajasthan Technical University.

Godavari Global University (formaly known as Godavari institute of Engineering and technology- GIET) is accredited by NAAC ‘A++' with 3.58/4 in the 3rd Cycle. GIET was established in the year 1998 and was confered with Godavari Global University status in the year 2024. However, GIET received many prestigious awards & recognitions from reputed agencies in India and abroad. It Ranked in the band 201-500 Engineering in NIRF ranking consecutively for 4 years since 2019. Furthermore, the University is recognized Under Sections 2(f) and 12(B) by UGC Act 1956.

Guru Nanak Dev Engineering College was founded in 1956 under the auspices of Nankana Sahib Education Trust (NSET), one of the most famous, earliest, and minority institutions in Northern India. Guru Nanak Dev Engineering College, a premier institution of higher learning, offers ME/M.Tech programs in the areas of engineering, IT & software, architecture & planning, and business & management studies. A curriculum centered on mechanical engineering, industrial engineering, production engineering, civil engineering, computer science engineering, electronics & communication engineering, information technology, VLSI design, power engineering, structural engineering, electrical engineering, environmental engineering, automobile engineering, mechanical engineering, and industrial engineering was established in the city of Punjab in 1956 to provide education and skills.

The IFET College of Engineering [IFET], founded in the year 1998, is a platinum category college located in Villupuram, Tamil Nadu. The NAAC accredited college is set up by eminent Industrialists, NRIs, and Indo French Educational Trust (IFET). The Autonomous College affiliated to Anna University offers both undergraduate and postgraduate courses in various disciplines. The College is also part of Cisco Networking Academy courses to enhance IT skills and promote career-building programs.

KMCT College of Engineering, established in 2001, is one of the most preferred engineering colleges in Kerala. It is affiliated to A.P.J Abdul Kalam Technological University and the University of Calicut. The College offers B.Tech at the Undergraduate level and M.Tech, MBA, MCA at the Postgraduate level. Admissions to the programs are purely based on entrance exams. The college has the right infrastructure and highly qualified faculty team to provide excellent technical education to its students.

KPR Institute of Engineering and Technology is an Autonomous Engineering Institution located in Arasur, Coimbatore. The Institution was established by KPR Charities in 2009 and is affiliated to Anna University, Chennai. The institute is accredited by NAAC and NBA. The institute has remarkable academic excellence and a significant placement record. The industry-driven Institution is certified by DSIR as the Scientific and Industrial Research Organization. KPRIET Coimbatore offers 8 UG Programs, 4 PG Programs and 6 Ph.D. Programs. The institution also provides hands-on training on life skills through Liberal Arts courses and Foreign Language courses.

Kathir College of Engineering was set up in the year 2008 at Coimbatore, Tamil Nadu. It is approved by AICTE and is affiliated to Anna University. The college offers B.E, B.Tech at the undergraduate level and ME, MBA at the post-graduate level. It provides quality education under highly-educated faculties with excellent academic experience. The college also maintained a good placement record over the years

College Name: Lakireddy Bali Reddy College of Engineering - [LBRCE]
Info Data: Lakireddy Bali Reddy College of Engineering (LBRCE) was established by Sri Lakireddy Bali Reddy in 1998. It is an autonomous college approved by AICTE and affiliated to Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University (JNTUK), Kakinada. This college is located in L.B Reddy Nagar, Krishna district, Mylavaram, Andhra Pradesh. It offers 8 UG courses and 6 PG courses. This institute offers admission to students in B.Tech. programmes on the basis of state level entrance examination EAMCET and M.Tech. programmes on the basis of GATE/PGECET score. It also offers admission to MBA and MCA programmes on the basis of ICET score.

MEA Engineering College was established in 2002 and is situated at Perinthalmanna, Malappuram, Kerala. It is the first NAAC accredited self-financing college in the engineering stream and has been awarded B+ Grade by the same. NBA has also accredited the college with 3 years of accreditation for CSE & MECH.

M. Kumarasamy College of Engineering has been established in the year 2000 by M. Kumarasamy Health and Educational Trust. It is the first engineering college to be established in the district of Karur. MKCE is affiliated to Anna University, approved by AICTE, New Delhi. It is an autonomous institution which is NAAC accredited and affiliated to Anna University, Chennai. The AICTE approved College is situated in Karur, Tamil Nadu. The nearest railway station is Karur Junction which is 12 Km far from the College.

College Name: Mahaveer Institute of Science and Technology- [MIST]
Info Data: Mahaveer Institute of Science and Technology (MIST) was established in the year of 2001. The institute holds its affiliation with Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University (JNTUH), Hyderabad. The college offers various UG, PG, and Diploma courses falling under the Engineering and Management disciplines. The institute offers various scholarships for students under many categories which adds as a plus point if you are looking for financial aids. The admissions are based strictly based on merit and entrance cut-off for both UG and PG Programs.

Mailam Engineering College, a self-financing institution has been established in 1998 and is situated in Villupuram in Tamil Nadu state of India. It is accredited from AICTE, TCS and it is affiliated to Anna University. MEC campus is spread over 42 Acres.
Manakula Vinayagar Institute of Technology was established in 2008 and is affiliated to Pondicherry University. It is approved by AICTE and India Today ranks the Institute at #170 for the year 2020.

College Name: Marthandam College of Engineering and Technology - [MACET]
Info Data: Marthandam College of engineering and technology has been established in 2006 and is in Kuttakuzhi , Tamil Nadu. MACET is approved by All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE), New Delhi and is affiliated to Anna University, Chennai and is an ISO 9001:2008 certified Institution. The goal of this college is to prepare skilled and intelligent employees for engineering industry and to make this college one of the best in engineering.

PA College of Engineering (PACE), Mangalore is a private engineering college established in the year 2000. It is approved by AICTE & affiliated to Visvesvaraya Technological University. The college offers B.Tech the UG level and M.Tech, MBA at the PG level, and Ph.D., M.Sc. at the research level. Besides these, the college also offers a Diploma in Engineering across 5 specializations. The college has a top-class infrastructure and a good placement record.

Rajagiri School of Engineering & Technology (RSET) is one of the leading educational institutions offering engineering education and research. It is located in the port city of Kochi, Kerala and was established in 2001. It offers B.Tech programs in 8 specializations, M.Tech programs in 5 specializations and PhD programs in 6 specializations.

Sahrdaya College of Engineering, Thrissur was established in 2002 under Irinjalakuda Diocesan Educational Trust. It is affiliated to Calicut University, Malappuram and approved by All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE), New Delhi. It is recognized by Government of Kerala and accredited by The Institution of Engineers, India. The vision of the SCET is to train the youth to be the leaders of tomorrow with apt skills, deep-rooted sense of social responsibility, strong ethical values and with a global outlook to face the challenges of changing world. The mission of the institute is to promote academic excellence, absolute discipline, and sound practical exposure.

Sanjivani College of Engineering, Ahmednagar, Maharashtra is working in the field of education to serve the society for the betterment of the nation. It aims at fostering professional technocrats who are skilled in their work and lead the nation with their aptitude. The college boasts diverse departments encompassing Civil Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Computer Engineering, Electronics and Computer Engineering, Information Technology, Mechatronics Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Engineering Science, Structural Engineering,and an advanced MBA, M.Tech, and PhD Research Centre. Sanjivani College of Engineering, Ahmednagar received Best College Award by SPPU, Pune in 2015.

Saroj Mohan Institute of Technology was established in the year 2003. The college is affiliated with Maulana Abul Kalam Azad University of Technology (MAKAUT). The institution is approved by AICTE, Directorate of Technical Education (DTE). College offers various Undergraduate courses in the field of Technology and regular courses in management and computer disciplines. The college conducts campus placements with companies like TCS, IBM, Verizon Mapline India, American Megatrend, Medtech. Admissions are offered on the WBJEE merit rank.

Seemanta Engineering College has been a pioneer of technical education for the tribal-dominated region at Mayurbhanj in Odisha. It has granted knowledge and excellence to North Orissa and the other adjoining states of West Bengal and Jharkhand. The institute got established in the year 1977 by the Seemanta Mahavidyalaya Samiti which was founded by Late Shri Paresh Chandra Basa. It is affiliated to Biju Patnaik University of Technology, Rourkela, Odisha and approved duly by AICTE, New Delhi and Government of Odisha. The institute's strong features include the beauty and bounties of nature in the foothills of the Simipal National Park with an exclusively diverse and exotic culture. The college provides for B.Tech, M.Tech and MCA courses in various disciplines along with other diploma degrees.

The Sengunthar Engineering College was established in 2001 to provide quality education in the field of engineering and technology. It offers UG, PG courses like BE, ME, M.Tech., MBA, MCA. Admission is based on entrance exams like TNEA, TANCET, GATE, CET, MAT, etc. The applications are available online.

Shivani Engineering college Tiruchirapalli is a college under the Shivani group of institutions started in 2009. It offers B.E. course in the 5 branches namely mechanical, computer science, electrical and electronics, electronics and communication, and bio-medical. The admission is based on the TNEA entrance exam. The students seeking admissions can apply through online mode for admission in this college.

Sri Venkateshwara College of Engineering is a self-financed institute located in Bengaluru and was established in 2001. It is approved by AICTE and Govt. of Karnataka and affiliated to Visvesvaraya Technological University(VTU), Belgaum. The campus is attractively landscaped in an 11 acre land at Vidyanagar, Kempegowda International Airport Road, Bengaluru.

College Name: TKR College of Engineering and Technology - [TKRCET]
Info Data: TKR College of Engineering And Technology, Hyderabad was established in 2002 and is affiliated to JNTU Hyderabad. The institute is AICTE approved, AICTE recognized, NBA and NAAC with ‘A’ grade accredited. TKR College of Engineering and Technology provides Diploma courses across 5 specializations, B.Tech courses across 8 specializations, MBA and M.Tech courses across 1 and 3 specializations respectively. Admissions to all courses are Entrance based.

Trinity College of Engineering, Kerala was established in 2011. It is approved by AICTE and affiliated under APJ Abdul Kalam Kerala Technological University. The college has been ranked as the Top College for Innovation and Entrepreneurship over the years by the Kerala Startup Mission (KSUM). Trinity College is also a mentor college for KSUM’s Startup Awareness and Leadership Training (SALT). Trinity College of Engineering offers B.Tech and B.Tech Lateral in Mechanical, Civil, EEE and ECE at Undergraduate level. Admission is based on valid scores in JEE Main/KEAM

APS Institution of Engineering (APSCE) is a professional institution in Bengaluru founded in 1997 by Acharya Pathasala Educational Trust (APSET). APSET is an organization with 88 years of history of providing quality education through a network of degree colleges, pre-universities, and schools. APS College of Engineering, shortly known as APSCE is a co-educational private college, affiliated to the Visvesvaraya Technological University, Belgaum, and accredited to the All India Council of Technical Engineering. APS College of Engineering is located on a 25-acre sprawling lush green campus, located in Bangalore, in Somanahalli, on Kanakapura Road.

College of Engineering, (COER Roorkee) was established by Seth Roshan Lal Jain Trust is the year 1998. The college offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses, namely, B.Tech. in eight different specializations and M.Tech. in two different specializations. There are 810 seats and 36 seats in B.Tech. and M.Tech., respectively.

College Name: Park College of Engineering and Technology - [PCET]
Info Data: Park College of Engineering and Technology was established in 1996. It is an AICTE accredited private college affiliated to Anna University, Chennai. It offers five main courses with different specialisations. The courses are for undergraduate and postgraduate.

College Name: University Institute of Information Technology, Himachal Pradesh University - [UIIT]
Info Data: University Institute of Information technology (UIIT) is a leading government institute for B.Tech in information technology programs in Northern India. The college has a close collaboration with the IT industry which helps the institute to give a competitive edge to other institutes. It offers B. TECH in five branches. The admission is done on the basis of marks obtained in the Entrance exam i. e. HPCET (Himachal Pradesh Common Entrance Test).

GD Goenka University (GDGU) is a private university established in the year 2013 in Gurgaon, Haryana. It is recognized by UGC, BCI, PCI, COA, NCTE, and ICAR. The university is approved by the Government of Haryana and achieved a QS IGUAGE “Diamond” rating. It holds the membership of AIU, ACU and IAU. The university is spread over an area of 60 acres. GD Goenka University offers more than 100 courses in the disciplines of Engineering, Management, Science, Design and many more. It has collaborated with 30+ universities and professional institutions in the USA, Canada, Australia, the UK and others. It has ten institutes offering higher education in various fields. GD Goenka University is awarded as the “” in India by ASSOCHAM.
NIILM University is a private university which is located in Kaithal in the state of Haryana, India. It was established by the Haryana State Legislature under Haryana Act No. 16 of 2011.

IEC University is a private university located at the HIMUDA education hub, near the village Kallujhanda, Solan district, Himachal Pradesh. IECU aim is to deliver multi-disciplinary world-class education through effective and efficient processes to make it accessible to all sections of the society. IEC University faculty is also well trained and experts in their respective fields.

ITM (SLS) Baroda University, Vadodara offers undergraduate, postgraduate and diploma courses in the discipline of Engineering, Science, Business, etc. Admissions will be done on the basis of merit and cutoff criteria of the institute.

ISL Engineering College, Hyderabad was established in the year 2008 and is approved by the AICTE. It is a private college and affiliated to Osmania University. It imparts quality education aiming to develop students as responsible citizens. It offers Bachelor of Technology across 6 specializations at the undergraduate level and also an MBA program at the post-graduate level. The college has excellent infrastructure and impressive placements

Trident Academy of Technology (TAT), Bhubaneswar was established in 2005.TAT is place where generations of Brilliant skills are discovered. Trident Academy of Technology, a name that has become a brand in the field of technical education, is today synonymous with excellence. Starting with the Academic Session 2014-15, the engineering college Trident Academy of Technology will introduce SIX SIGMA practices in some of its methodologies

Established in 2013 under Rajasthan State Government Act, Maulana Azad University is a leading state private university located in Jodhpur. The University has been a global knowledge center and boasts of educating more than 8000 students in multiple disciplines like Pharmacy, Technology, Management, Education, Science, Commerce, Arts etc.

Himalayan University Itanagar is a State Private University, founded by the Jean foundation in 2013, established under Sec 2(F) of UGC Act, 1956, by the Government of Arunachal Pradesh at the Nahalagun in Itanagar, Arunachal Pradesh. The University provides various courses in almost every theme of major disciplines such as B.Sc., M.Sc., BCA, MCA, BBA, MBA, BA, MA, B.Com, M.Com, etc.

People's University is one of India's leading professional and research-driven private universities as well as one of the biggest single-campus universities situated in Bhopal, Madhya Pradesh. It has 10 constituent institutes that offer 25 courses along the Science stream, 7 courses along with Commerce stream, and 6 courses along the Arts streams. Both UG as well as PG courses like MBBS/ MD, B.Sc/ M.Sc, BDS, BBA/ MBA, B-tech/ M-tech, B.Sc Nursing/ M.Sc Nursing, BPT/ MPT, LLM & Ph.D,. etc can be obtained. Admissions to these courses are based on merit as well as entrance exams like NEET-UG & PG.

Established in 2002, Amrita School of Engineering offers B.Tech., M.Tech. and Ph.D. programs in a large number of disciplines. It has been accredited with the highest rating of 'A' by NAAC and is affiliated to Amrita Vishwa Vidyapeetham. Located in Bangalore, it is one of the top ranked private universities in India and provides 95% placement to its students.

Ganga Group of Institutions was founded in 1989 under the aegis of Pawan Ganga Educational Society. GGI is approved by UGC,  AICTE, COA and NCTE. The institute is accredited with NAAC A grade and NBA. Ganga Group of Institutions offers UG and PG courses in several specializations. Courses like B.Tech, BBA, BCA, B.Arch are offered as undergraduate courses and M.Tech, MBA, MCA, M.Arch and M.Ed as post graduate courses. All the Courses offered by the university are affiliated to MDU, Rohtak.

RajaRajeswari College of Engineering, founded in 2006 and based in Bengaluru, is affiliated with Visvesvaraya Technological University (VTU) in Belgaum. The College is approved by the All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE), New Delhi, Government of Karnataka, and has an ISO 9001-2008 certification. It is managed by Moogambigai Charitable and Education Trust (MCET), Bangalore. With approved engineering branches like CSE, ECE, EEE, and ME, the institute has worldwide accreditation from HLCAT, Texas, USA, and .Rajarajeswari College of Engineering, Bengaluru, Karnataka, offers 8 UG Programs, 3 PG Programs, and 9 Research Programs in various Engineering, Management, and Computer Applications. The ./ programs last four years, and the M.E/M. Tech programs for two years, and the MCA and MBA programs for two years.  include B.Sc. (Honors), B.E. in Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning, B.E. in Robotics & Automation, and B.E. in CSE (IoT) Cybersecurity Inc. Sri Manakula Vinayagar Engineering College (SMVEC), situated in the Puducherry Union Territory, is an engineering and management college offering 14 B.Tech programs, 8 postgraduate programs including MBA and MCA and 11 Research programs (PhD). All the B.Tech UG and PG programs including M.Tech, MCA & MBA are approved by AICTE New Delhi & UGC, and affiliated to Pondicherry University.

College Name: International Institute of Technology and Management - [IITM]
Info Data: International Institute of Technology & Management (IITM) was established in the year 2010. The institute is approved by AICTE, New Delhi & HSBTE, Panchkula and affiliated to DCRUST University, Murthal. It is accredited A grade by NAAC. The sprawling campus is located 10 kms from Sonepat city. The college offers courses in the field of science, technology, engineering, management and pharmacy. The campus is spread its wings in 13 acres of land on the Delhi-Amritsar National Highway and it is just 40 kms from Delhi.

Shobhit University is a private university established in the year 2012 at Gangoh, Uttar Pradesh. It has been accredited by NAAC with a ‘A’ Grade. The university offers a variety of undergraduate, postgraduate and doctoral programs under various departments that include Engineering, Law, Management, Computer Applications, Pharmacy, Education & more. The degree awarded by Shobhit University are recognised by University Grants Commission (UGC) and approved by AICTE. Shobhit University has ranked in India's Top 27 Technical Universities in India Today University Ranking 2022. The institute also ranked in India's Top 5 Technical Universities (highest number of Patent published in the past three years) in India Today University Ranking 2022. Further, the Law Programmes offered by the institute are recognised by Bar Council of India.

Maharishi University of Information Technology (MUIT), established in 2001, is well-known for disseminating quality education to students. The university falls under flagship of Maharishi Group. The group has 200 schools spread over 17 states in 174 cities all over India. Nearly 1,00,000 students are enrolled in them. The University offers Diploma in Engineering, B.Tech, M.Tech, BBA, MBA, BCA, MCA, B.Com, M.Com, B.Sc, M.Sc & Ph.D Courses. Read: MUIT Admissions

Established in 2006, Vidya Knowledge Park is located in Meerut, Uttar Pradesh. It is affiliated with Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam Technical University, Lucknow. and Chaudhary Charan Singh University, Meerut. The college offers a range of programs, both undergraduate as well as postgraduate courses. Vidya Knowledge Park, Meerut has 8 different schools of its own such as Vidya College of Engineering, Vidya School of Business, Vidya School of Fashion Technology, etc. Several courses are offered through these institutions. The major courses offered by the Vidya Knowledge Park, Meerut include B.Tech, MCA, MBA, and BBA with various specializations. All courses and the college itself are approved by AICTE.

Jaypee University, located in Anoopshahr, Uttar Pradesh was founded in the year 2014. The university offers UG courses like B.Tech., B.Com., BA, BBA, B.Sc. in various specialisations. Jaypee University Anoopshahr also offers doctoral level Ph.D. courses in 4 streams.

St. Joseph University was established in 2016 under govt. act. no. 6. It is a private, catholic research university run by DMI (Daughter of Mary Immaculate) sisters and MMI (Missionaries of Mary Immaculate) fathers with a genuine aim of providing education to the people of Nagaland. The university is recognised by UGC (University Grants Commission) and approved by AICTE (All India Council for Technical Education).

Rishihood University, Sonipat established in the year 2020 is the first and only impact university in India. Rishihood University is approved by University Grants Commission (UGC) and focuses on creativity, entrepreneurship, and leadership in the students. The university offers B. Des., B.Sc (Hons) Psychology, Makers Undergrad BBA, and B.Tech at the UG level. Admission to all the UG programs is done based on aptitude tests and personal interviews.

Sarala Birla University (SBU), Ranchi is a self-financed private university. It was established in the year 2017. There are several academic schools under SBU named School of Engineering & Computer Sciences, School of Humanities & Linguistics, School of Commerce & Business Management, School of Legal Studies, School of Pharmacy, and School of Yoga & Naturopathy. Presently, the university offers BTech, BPharm, B.Sc, BA, BBA, BCA, B.Com, BPA, LLB, Integrated-LLB, MBA, LLM, MCA, M.Sc, MA, M.Com, MPA, and PhD courses. Besides, it also offers a Diploma in Engineering, Pharmacy, and other specializations.
Radha Govind University is a private institution located in Ramgarh, Jharkhand. It was established in 2018 with the aim of empowering the youth of Jharkhand.

College Name: Kavikulguru Institute of Technology and Science - [KITS]

As per Times of India Ranking Survey, Stanley College of Engineering and Technology for Women is Top Pvt Engineering Institutes in AP& Telangana.

College Name: Aditya Institute of Technology and Management -[AITAM] Tekkali

The college provides undergraduate degrees for 8 subjects and 2 postgraduate degrees. Check Anand Engineering College Admissions

College Name: Baba Banda Singh Bahadur Engineering College - [BBSBEC]
Info Data: Baba Banda Singh Bahadur Engineering College has earned accreditation from the NBA for various programs. Major IT companies TCs, Zscaler, SED, Trangile, Wipro, Reliance, Mindtree, Infosys, Nestle, IBM, HCL etc. Admissions are offered strictly based on the JEE merit list generated by the college administration for B.Tech courses. Last year's cut-off rank for general students was around 73792. The college also offers establishment and Vocational courses that teach and grant the most elevated qualities to students.

College Name: Bangalore College of Engineering and Technology-[BCET]
Info Data: Bangalore College of Engineering and Technology(BCET) is situated in Bangalore, Karnataka. The college was established in the year 2000.

Bankura Unnayani Institute of Engineering, Bankura, West Bengal was inaugurated by the chief minister of West Bengal in the year of 1998. The institute offers BCA, B.Sc, B.Voc and undergraduate and post graduate courses in the field of engineering.

Chadalawada Ramanamma Engineering College (CREC) is a private autonomous college of engineering founded in 2004. It is located at Tirupati, Andhra Pradesh and is affiliated to Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University, Anantapur. The college is approved by AICTE & accredited with ‘A Grade by NAAC. It offers B.Tech at the UG level and M.Tech, MBA, MCA at the PG level. The college is equipped with outstanding infrastructure and has a training & placement cell.

College Name: Chettinad College of Engineering and Technology - [CCET]
Info Data: The Chettinad College of Engineering and Technology, also known as CCET, is a private institute in Karur, Tamil Nadu.
