The UG admissions are based on TNEA counseling, while TANCET scores are accepted for PG courses. The top recruiters of the college include Amazon, Infosys, and Wipro, among many others.

College Name: College of Engineering And Management, Kolaghat
Info Data: College of Engineering and Management, Kolaghat (CEMK) is a private institution located in Kolaghat, West Bengal, India. Established in 1998, by the “Vidyasagar Society for Integrated Learning (VSIL)”, Kolkata, and is affiliated with the Maulana Abul Kalam Azad University of Technology (MAKAUT), formerly known as West Bengal University of Technology. The college was developed within the integrated complex of a large Thermal Power Station, e.g. Kolaghat Thermal Power Station, under the able leadership of Prof. S. K. Sen, the founding Chairman of VSIL and the then Minister in-charge, Power, Science & Technology and Non-Conventional Energy Sources.

College Name: DAV Institute of Engineering and Technology - [DAVIET]
Info Data: DAV Institute of Engineering and Technology, Jalandhar, popularly known as DAVIET is an engineering institute established in the year 2001. At DAVIET, the students are provided with the best professional education, right skills, high moral values, sound intellectual powers, refined analytical and decision making skills. The university is envisioned to attain the coveted status of a growth-oriented resource of national importance known for quality professional education, research, and innovation. The college is duly recognized by the UGC u/s 2(F), 2017, AICTE for its technical courses and accredited by NAAC ‘A+’ grade. Sprawling over 18 acres piece of land, the institution is affiliated to . The university offers numerous  in different fields of Engineering & Technology, Business Administration, Computer Applications, Hotel Management, and Commerce, etc.

Info Data: Ellenki Institute of Engineering & Technology was founded in the year 1999 in Hyderabad about 18 kilometers from JNTUH Kukatpally. The college is granted autonomous status by UGC and approved by the All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE), New Delhi, and affiliated to Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University, Hyderabad (JNTUH). As per the latest reports, the college has been rated 4.5 stars by the Institution Innovation Council, Ministry of Education, Government of India, and has achieved a ranking in the Atal Ranking of Institutions on Innovation Achievements (ARIIA).

College Name: GKM College of Engineering and Technology - [GKMCET]
Info Data: GKM College of Engineering and Technology, affiliated to Anna University Chennai, is a private university located in Chennai, Tamil Nadu. It was established in 1996 and it has been accredited by NAAC with grade ‘A’. GKM College of Engineering and Technology offers multiple courses under the UG, PG as well as Ph.D. domains. The college provides around 10 specializations for UG and PG levels and 4 specializations at the Ph.D. level.

College Name: G L Bajaj Institute of Technology and Management
Info Data: G.L. Bajaj Institute of Technology & Management Noida is a prestigious Institute established in the year 2007. Tech, MBA, and MCA at the PG level.

Karpagam Institute of Technology was established in the year 2007, by Dr.R. Vasantha Kumar and is accredited by AICTE, NAAC and NBA and takes its affiliation from the state technical university of Tamil Nadu, Anna University (AU). It offers B.E and B.Tech courses.

College Name: Kongunadu College of Engineering and Technology - [KNCET]
Info Data: Kongunadu College of Engineering and Technology (KCET), is a private technical institution established in 2007. It was awarded as National Level Clean and Smart Campus Award-2019 by AICTE. The college offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses in engineering.

MBM Engineering College or Mugneeram Bangur Memorial Engineering College is a pioneer technical institute established in 1951 by Rajasthan Govt. It is affiliated to Jai Narain Vyas University, Jodhpur. Presently, it is running B.Tech & B.Arch. at the UG level and MCA and M.Tech at the PG level. Some of the courses have the approval of AICTE and is granted by UGC. The CSE Department of MBM College has collaboration with IBM USA for student’s training

College Name: Rajadhani Institute of Engineering and Technology - [RIET] Attinga

College Name: SCMS School of Engineering and Technology [SSET]

Admission to the BE program is done through the JEE exam score followed by counseling. For admission in Diploma in engineering, the admission is based on the merit obtained in the qualifying examination.

College Name: Silver Oak College of Engineering and Technology - [SOCET]

It is the constituent college of Silver Oak Group of Institutions (SOGI), Ahmedabad and has a sister college, namely Aditya Silver Oak Institute of Technology (ASOIT), Ahmedabad. Sri Siddhartha Institute of Technology is a premier Institute located in Tumkur, Karnataka. The institute is accredited by NAAC A+ grade and NBA. SSIT offers B.E, M.Tech, MCA and Ph. D across the branches of Engineering. Apart from this, SSIT also offers a 2 years MBA program. Admissions to the UG programs are based on KCET and UGET, while admissions to the PG programs are through PGCET. The Institute also provides good placement and job opportunities by inviting many multinational companies. As per the latest placement report, the highest package offered was INR 12 LPA. Companies like TCS, Infosys, HCL, Cognizant, HP, First American are some of the top recruiters of SSIT.

The college is the first self-financed college in Tamilnadu in the field of Engineering. For admission to UG courses, college accepts entrance of TNEA and for PG courses they accept TANCET which are conducted by Anna University.

Thangavelu Engineering College was established in the year 1995 by Ponniamman Educational Trust and the TJ Educational Trust with the objective of producing high-quality Engineers and Technocrats. It offers several undergraduate, postgraduate, diploma courses in a number of specializations.

Kalaignar Karunanidhi Institute of Technology (KIT) Coimbatore was established in 2008. The College offers UG and PG Courses such as B.E, M.Tech, MCA and MBA . Some of the eminent recruiters who had visited the Institute are Jabong, Concierge Technology, Universal Hunt, Micromax, ICICI, TCS, and many more. Candidates can apply to this Institute online as well as offline.

Established by the ­­­Government of Himachal Pradesh in 2012, the Career Point University, Hamirpur provides courses in the field of Engineering and technology, Computer Application and IT, Basic and Applied Sciences, Business & Managements, Vocational and Legal Studies. It offers a variety of Undergraduate, Post-graduate & Doctoral courses in fields such as Engineering and Technology, Management, Commerce, Applied Sciences, Computer Applications, Humanities, and Social sciences are available. The university has the word-class infrastructure and aims to provide quality education under a strong team of qualified faculty members.

College Name: Sri Guru Granth Sahib World University - [SGGSWU]
Info Data: Sri Guru Granth Sahib World University (SGGSWU) is located in Fatehgarh Sahib, Punjab. It offers a wide array of undergraduate, postgraduate and doctoral courses like B.Tech, M.Tech, B.C.A, M.C.A, P.G.D.C.A, B.Sc., M.Sc. B.Com., M.Com., BBA, MBA BA, MA, PhD and many more.

It is located on a 100-acre campus with all modern amenities. SPSU has a current strength of nearly 750 students (excluding 79 Ph.D Scholars) and 54 faculty members. The current student-to-teacher ratio at SPSU is 14:1. The university has two schools: School of Engineering and School of Management, both offering programs at the undergraduate, postgraduate and doctoral levels. Admission to courses is granted on the basis of the score obtained in the SPSAT entrance exam conducted by the university.

Vinayaka Missions University, also known as the Vinayaka Mission’s Research Foundation (VMRF), is a NAAC accredited deemed to be university under section 3 of the UGC Act of 1956 located in Salem, Tamil Nadu. The university was established in 1981 by philanthropist Dr. A. Shanmugasundaram as “Thirumuruga Kirupananda Variyar Thavathiru Sundara Swamigal (TKVTSS) Medical Educational and Charitable Trust”. A vibrant university with a multi-cultural experience, it got its “deemed to be” status in 2001. With the motto of “Vision, Wisdom, Unity”, the university aims to spread education globally in the fields of Medicine, Dentistry, Paramedical, Homeopathy, Engineering, Management, and Basic Science.

Jyothy Institute of Technology (JIT), located in Bangalore, India, is a private engineering college that was established in the year 2011. The college is affiliated to Visvesvaraya Technological University (VTU) and approved by the All-India Council for Technical Education (AICTE).

The college is positioned at 19th in KTU out of 150 colleges in Kerala. The institute offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses under various specializations of engineering. Admission to the college is done on the basis of marks secured in the respective entrance exams.

Info Data: The admission criteria is strictly entrance based. EAMCET is accepted for B.Tech and PGCET or GATE for M.Tech. Top MNCs offer admission at this college, the highest package for previous year recruitment was recorded at INR 12 LPA.

DSEU Okhla II Campus offers multiple programs at the UG and PG levels which include BTech, MTech, and diploma programs. The institute offers a 4-year long BTech program under 3 different specialisations. Admission to this program is based on the JEE Mains and IPU CET scores. Also, the DSEU Okhla II Campus offers an MTech program at the PG level in the Tool Engineering discipline. The institute accepts GATE scores for admission to its MTech program. The college also provides a diploma course in Mechanical Engineering and the admission procedure is strictly based on the marks and merits obtained in the qualifying exams.

College Name: K. C. College of Engineering And Management Studies And Research
Info Data: KC College of Engineering and Management Studies and Research was established in 2001. It also offers post-graduation courses in MMS / MBA. Admissions are accepted online, based on the JEE examination or MHT CET. Application for admission is accepted online through the official website.

College Name: Birla Institute of Technology Extension Centre - [BIT]
Info Data: Birla Institute of Technology Deoghar is a constituent college of Birla Institute of Technology and a Jharkhand based premier educational institute which came into existence in October 2007 as a result of MOU signed between Government of Jharkhand and BIT to roll out intellectual brilliance in the State.

College Name: A. P. Shah Institute of Technology - [APSIT]
Info Data: A.P. Shah Institute of Technology (APSIT), Thane, Maharashtra is a private engineering college that was established in the year 2014. APSIT is affiliated with the University of Mumbai and approved by the All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE). APSIT offers undergraduate programs in various engineering disciplines including Computer Engineering, Information Technology, Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning, Data Science, Mechanical Engineering, and Civil Engineering. Admissions are based on the JEE Mains or the MH - CET.

College Name: Vidyavardhini's College of Engineering and Technology - [VCET]
Info Data: Vidyavardhini College of engineering and technology (VCET) is a private institute established in 1994. It is affiliated to the University of Mumbai and has been accredited by NAAC with ‘B+’ grade. The college offers B.Tech across six disciplines at the undergraduate level. The admissions are purely on the basis of the candidate’s merit in entrance exams.

Vimal Jyothi Engineering College (VJEC), was established in 2002 and it is managed by Meshar Diocesan Educational Trust. The college offers courses in different streams in B.Tech, M.Tech, and Ph.D. Admission is based on marks secured in the Engineering Entrance Exam conducted by Commissioner of Entrance Exams, Govt. of Kerala and for M.Tech candidates should be a B.Tech graduate or equivalent Degree in relevant stream. VJEC Kannur offers placement for deserving students with an average salary of INR 4.25 LPA in the year 2019 to 2020.

K. Ramakrishnan College of Engineering (KRCE), Tiruchirappalli was established in 2008, affiliated to AU, Chennai and approved by AICTE. It offers various undergraduate and postgraduate courses in the stream of Engineering, Technology and Management. Admission to KRCE Trichy is done on the basis of TANCET and TNEA scores. In addition to this, the institute has a dedicated training and placement cell. Some of the top recruiters are Infosys, Justdial, L&T Infotech, TCS, Amazon, Wipro, ICICI Bank, etc.

Ganga Technical Campus also known as GTC was established in 2012. Situated in Bahadurgarh, Haryana it is affiliated to Maharshi dayanand university (MDU), Rohtak and approved by AICTE New Delhi. The college offers many courses in the engineering and IT sector like B.tech BCA, M.Tech, Diploma. The college also provides management courses like BBA and MBA. The Ganga Technical Campus (GTC) is a well known private university for engineering.

Pratap University, Jaipur, established in the year 2011 with the permission of the Rajasthan Government, offers admissions both to domestic and international students. PU is recognised by University Grants Commission (UGC) and Member of All India Universities (AIU). The University has international tie-ups with the University of Donja Gorica, Montenegro.

College Name: Girijananda Chowdhury Institute of Management & Technology - [GIMT]
Info Data: Girijananda Chowdhury Institute of Management and Technology - GIMT Guwahati, established in 2006 by the Shrimanta Shankar Academy Society. GIMT Guwahati offers courses in undergraduate, postgraduate, Ph.D. programs. At the UG level, it provides B.Tech., BBA, B.Sc, BCA. Under PG program courses are in MBA, MCA, M.Tech.

GIET Engineering College, is a Private College which was established in the year 1998 and located in the serene and sylvan suburbs region of Rajahmundhry of East Godavari City of Andhra Pradesh. It is a premier engineering college in the state of Andhra Pradesh with world-class education standards. Sprawling in the huge 300 acres of lush green environment, GIET campus reflects the finest educational facilities around. The college is ISO Certified, NBA-accredited, NAAC ‘A’ grade accredited and many other distinctions as well to add charm to GIET campus’ glory.

Godavari Institute of Engineering and Technology (GIET) was set up in 1989 to provide high-class engineering education. It has been developed throughout the year to be included among the top institutes in Andhra Pradesh state. Situated near the scenic serene atmosphere at Chaitanya Nagar, Rajahmundry on NH-16.

College Name: Babu Banarasi Das Northern India Institute of Technology - [BBDNIIT]
Info Data: BBDNIIT or Babu Banarasi Das Northern India Institute of Technology, Lucknow established in 1999 is a private institute that offers many courses on the Undergraduate level, postgraduate level, and diploma courses. The courses offered by BBDNITT, Lucknow include B.Pharma, MBA, and M.Tech.

Narsimha Reddy Engineering College (NRCM) was established in the year 2007 with the aim of providing quality higher education. It is affiliated to Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University, Hyderabad and approved by AICTE. The college has received Autonomous approval from UGC and is ranked among the top 25 colleges in Telangana by Times of India Survey. It offers B.Tech at the UG level & M.Tech, MBA programs at the PG level. All the B.Tech courses are accredited by NBA. The college has maintained a satisfactory placement record over the years.

The KGiSL Institute of Technology was established in the year 2008. It was established by the KG Trust and sponsored by KG Information Systems Private Limited. Located in a 40-acre campus the college also has software-related operations and opportunities for students. The college is famous for its courses in Engineering and Technology. The niche of the course program is the technical and practical experience offered by the institute. Along with classroom teaching the college also offers Moodle and eLearning facilities to the students.

College Name: Jai Parkash Mukand Lal Innovative Engineering & Technology Institute - [JMIETI]
Info Data: Jai Prakash Mukand Lal Innovative Engineering & Technology Institute (JMIETI) is known for providing quality education in the field of Engineering & Technology. It is located in Radaur which is 18 km from Yamuna Nagar and 28 km from Kurukshetra.

SAL College of Engineering (SCE Ahmedabad), commenced its programs in 2012 under the guidance of SAL Education. SALCE Ahmedabad offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses namely, B.E and M.E. Admission to the courses is based on three entrances exams. The entrance exams accepted for admission are GUJCET and JEE Main for the UG programs and GATE exam score for PG programs. Applicants may apply online as well as offline for the admission process by submitting the mandatory documents along with the application form.

OP Jindal University (OPJU), established by Jindal Group, is at a fast pace striving to make a mark in the delivery of outstanding education and research. Established in 2014, OP Jindal University is a private institution that provides courses such as Diploma, B.Tech., BBA, and B.Sc. courses at the undergraduate level and M.Tech. MBA and MSc. at the postgraduate level. The curriculum of all the courses is based on National Education Policy (NEP).

Gopal Narayan Singh University (GNSU) Sasaram, was established in the year 2018, It is one of the six private universities in Bihar. The college is recognized by the University Grants Commission. The institution supports and believes in providing the best education in every field, they have 50+ acres of campus that encompasses a cutting edge Faculty in Medical College & Hospital, Management Studies, Commerce, Nursing, Information Technology, Law, Pharmacy, Paramedical Sciences, Agriculture Science, Mass Communication & Journalism, Department of Library & Information Sciences, and the Department of Education. The private university offers courses in Under Graduation, Post Graduation, Diploma, Integrated, and Doctoral.

Shyam University (SU), Dausa, Rajasthan, was established in the year 2018, under the recognition of the University Grants Commission(UGC). The institution is affiliated to AICTE, PCI, NCTE and approved under the government of Rajasthan. The University is spread over 38.25 acres of land surrounded by Aravali Hills in pollution-free, lush green and eco-friendly environment.

College Name: KIPM College of Engineering and Technology - [KIPM]
Info Data: KIPM College of Engineering & Technology was established in under the aegis of Ashutosh Shiksha Evam Sewa Sansthan in the benevolent guidance and leadership of Mr. R. D. Singh, to provide quality education to the students of management. The Institute has a sprawling campus spanning over 5.84 acres of land .It has two academic blocks. The Institute is located in an excellent high greens surroundings at GIDA, Gorakhpur.

College Name: Chalapathi Institute of Engineering and Technology - [CIET]
Info Data: Chalapathi Institute of Engineering and Technology, Guntur was started in the year 2007 under the aegis of Chalapathi Educational Society with an objective to promote proper education which is useful for society. College is affiliated to Acharya Nagarjuna University and is approved by AICTE.

College Name: KKR & KSR Institute of Technology and Sciences - [KITS]
Info Data: KKR and KSR Institute of Technology and Sciences was established in 2008. The institute is affiliated to JNTU – K. The institute has been imparting the knowledge about the latest professional practices since its inception. With an eye on the changing trends and thereby maintaining the original standards, the institute has been nurturing students to become professionally equipped to face the global challenges. The institute has embedded the interactive learning pedagogies in the education system and has been delivering the most optimum student teacher ratio. The focus is to produce technocrats for global industry.

Kallam Haranadhareddy Institute of Technology (KHIT), established in 2010, is a private institution located in Guntur, Andhra Pradesh. The college is approved by the All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE) and is affiliated to Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University (JNTUK), Kakinada.

Vikrant University, Gwalior is a UGC-recognized university approved by the AICTE, UGC, Bar Council of India, Pharmacy Council of India and the MP Private University Regulatory Commission. The university has a strong reputation for academic excellence and has received several awards and accolades, including the Captain of Industry Award (MP), Global Innovation Award (UAE) and Eminence Award (MP). Vikrant University has been honored with the prestigious Award of the "Best University for Sustainable Future Education" by the Indian Institutional Ranking Framework (IIRF). Further, VU has been recognised in the India Private Multidisciplinary Universities Rankings - 2024 and ranked among the top 300 private universities in India.

JIS University, Kolkata is ranked in 100-125 Band in NIRF Ranking for Pharmaceutical Technologies in 2023, MHRD(GOI). JIS University offers undergraduate, postgraduate and diploma courses in the specialized fields of Science, Engineering & Technology, Pharmacy, Management, Law, Social Sciences and Education. Admission to the JIS University done on the basis of merit, entrance examination and cutoff criteria of the institute. The University provides PhD programs in various courses as well. The University always encourages entrepreneurship and skill development among the students for promoting entrepreneurship, employability and self-employment.

Renaissance University Indore, Madhya Pradesh, formerly known as Indore Indira Business School is one of the newest private universities in central India. The university has a total of 10 departments, 34-course streams and 60000+ graduates around the globe. The university offers courses as Bachelor’s, Master’s, Diploma, and certification programs. The admission process is available online as well as offline. Admission is done on the basis of marks scored in national levels entrance exams like CAT, MAT, ATMA, XAT, and MPMET.

OmDayal Group of Institution (ODGI), Kolkata was established in 2010 and affiliated to MAKAUT, Kolkata. The institute offers AICTE & COA approved undergraduate courses in the disciplines of Engineering, Architecture, Computer Applications, and Management. Admission to ODGI Kolkata is done on the basis of WBJEE, JEE Main, CET/ NATA scores. The institute has a dedicated placement cell that provides 100% placement assistance to the students. The highest package offered to the students is INR 9.0 LPA. Some of the top recruiters are Accenture, Capgemini, Ambuja Cement, Amazon, Hero, Hitachi, Infosys etc.

AVC College of Engineering was established in the year 1996 in the Nagpattnam district of Tamil Nadu with a mission to become the center of technical and academic excellence. It is currently managed by A V charities which have been working towards imparting the quality education since 1955. The learning modules are directly linked with the R& D department in order to evolve the patterns and make it more students oriented.

AWH Engineering College, Calicut is a Private College established in the year 2001 with a sole purpose of appreciating engineers of admirable traits and craft strong foundation for engineering philosophy, innovative research competence and exemplary professional wisdom. The institution is fully affiliated to APJ Abdul Kalam Technological University, Thiruvananthapuram and committed to supporting the educated to gain acquaintance and widen their dexterity and potential. Calicut is a beautiful coastal city known for its true originality and is ideal for edification. The institution works with the mission to see the reimbursement of superiority in technical edification, reach the underprivileged and minority division of the residents and to develop superior ethics and values in the corporate profession. The college offers  in numerous disciplines along with an MCA Program.

Aarupadai Veedu Institute of Technology (AVIT), Chennai was established in the year 1998 as an affiliated institution under the Vinayaka mission university. Later it was affiliated to the Anna University, Chennai. In 2004, the institution was included in the ambit of Vinayaka Missions University, Salem. The institution is committed to impart quality education to the students from different socio-economic backgrounds. The institute is ISO 9001:2008 certified.

College Name: Abacus Institute of Engineering and Management
Info Data: Abacus Institute of Engineering and Management is a private funded management and technical Institute. It was established in 2003 by some social workers and educationist to create a ‘Center for Excellence’.

College Name: Akshaya College of Engineering and Technology-[ACET]

Info Data: Al Ameen Engineering College, Erode was established in 1984 under Al-Ameen Educational and Charitable Trust. It is affiliated to Anna University, Coimbatore and approved by All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE), New Delhi. It is an ISO 9001:2008 Certified Institute. The vision of the college is to evolve as a globally competent technical university and to build centre of excellence in engineering, technology, applied science and management. The mission of the college is to achieve sterling standards in academics, research and other social service activities besides being poised to produce outstanding and holistic professionals. The college campus is spread over an area of 13.33 acre and surrounded by the green environment. It is located at a distance of 10 km from Erode railway station and bus stand.

College Name: Rajadhani Institute of Science and Technology - [RIST]

Info Data: Amrutvahini College of Engineering was established in the year 1983 by Amrutvahini Shoti and Shikshan Santha to provide a distinctive excellence driven technical education that will groom future generations

Arasu Engineering College was established in 2000 by Sri Thirunavukkarasu Dhanalakshmi Educational and Charitable Trust. It is the first Engineering College started in the Kumbakonam. It started with the aim to accelerate academic, social and economic development.

College Name: Arya College of Engineering and IT - [ACEIT]
Info Data: Arya College of Engineering and IT (ACEIT) is one of the leading institutes of national significance located in Jaipur, Rajasthan. ACEIT is accredited by NAAC and approved by the AICTE and accredited by NAAC. Established in 2000, the college has also been accredited with an ‘A’ grade by affiliating university since the inception of QIV. Arya College of Engineering and IT is affiliated to the Rajasthan Technological University (RTU), Kota. ACEIT offers UG and PG courses in the field of Engineering and Management. The flagship courses of ACEIT a B.Tech program across several specializations and an M.Tech degree course. Candidates with Diploma in Engineering can also opt for lateral entry to the B,Tech course. ACEIT also runs an MBA degree program across 3 specializations. The institute shortlists candidates on the basis of scores for the B.tech program. However, admission to the M.Tech course depends on candidate’s performance in GATE.  Admission to the courses at ACEIT is done through the entrance examination. The institute accepts CAT scores for MBA admission.

College Name: Bapuji Institute of Engineering and Technology - [BIET]
Info Data: Bapuji institute of engineering and technology, davangere, was established in the year 1958 is one of the oldest and best technological institutes of the Karnataka. Bapuji institute of engineering and technology is for those students who wants to get the best education and also have desire to get success in their technological career and who wants to get the best technological skills in their lives. This college has been known best for its foals of attracting the students in the area of technological education. The vision of this college is to help the young minds to get excellence in their career.The Bapuji institute of engineering and technology provides excellence in education.

Cape Institute of Technology was established in 2001. The basic objective of Cape is to integrate the analytical skills of the student and enable them to reinvent creating ideas, thereby creating Engineers of tomorrow. Cape' is the brain child of a long ventured dream of great men and scholars which has been started at the tail end of the landscape "Cape Comorin" which aims at fostering.

Dhanlakshmi College of Engineering, Chennai was started under the aegis of Dhanlakshmi Education Trust in the academic year 2001-2002.  College has grown into distinguished center for engineering and technological studies. Institute strives to provide student quality technical education that moulds him into a good professional engineer.

Dhirajlal Gandhi College of Technology (DGCT) is a private college which is located in Salem, Tamil Nadu. It is approved by All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE) and accredited by the National Assessment and Accreditation Council (NAAC) with ‘A’ grade. The college is affiliated to Anna University Chennai. It offers 4-year degree courses (B.E.) in 7 Engineering disciplines viz. Agriculture Engineering, Civil Engineering, Electrical & Electronics Engineering, Electronics & Communication Engineering, Computer Science & Engineering and Mechanical Engineering (B.Tech) in Artificial Intelligence & Data Science. At the PG level, the college offers 4 M.E. courses viz. Structural Engineering, Communication Systems, Computer Science & Engineering and CAD / CAM. All courses offered by Dhirajlal Gandhi College of Technology are approved by the All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE)New Delhi.

Dronacharya College of Engineering (DCE), Gurgaon was established in 1998 by Smt Anguri Devi Charitable Trust. Dronacharya College of Engineering is approved by the All-India Council for Technical Education (AICTE) and is affiliated with Gurugram University (GU). The institute is recognized under 12(f) and 2(b) by University Grant Commission (UGC) Act 1956 and ISO Certified for 21001-2018 and 10001-2004. It has also received accreditation from NBA and NAAC. The college received a Certificate of Appreciation Categorized as a Band  under the category "Colleges/Institutes (Private / Self-Financed) (Technical)" in Atal Ranking of Institutions on Innovation Achievements (ARIIA) 2021 by MHRD. DCE also received “Outstanding Institution Award” from NITTTR Chandigarh for 2012-13 & 2022-23 session.

EGS Pillay Engineering College was started in the year 1995 under the sponsorship of G. S. Pillay & Sons Educational and Charitable Trust. College has gained the reputation of being most preferred engineering college by the students. College is approved by the AICTE, New Delhi and is affiliated to Anna University. It is ISO 9001:2008 certified.

Einstein College of Engineering was founded in 2004 by Late Mr. Aladi Aruna, former Law Minister of Tamilnadu. The college is  offering 5 UG courses and 6 PG courses in Engineering as well as MBA programme.

Eswar College Of Engineering has been established in 2008 on chilakaluripet road just 5KM from Narasaraopet, Guntur of Andhra Pradesh with a motto to produce such engineers who can contribute to the growth of the nation with their creativity and skills. So to fulfill the motto, the college has made advancement in the field of education technique and infrastructural facility.

College Name: G Narayanamma Institute of Technology and Science - [GNITS]
Info Data: G.Narayanamma Institute of Technology and Science also known as GNITS Hyderabad is a leading Engineering college in Hyderabad which was founded by the late Sri G.Pulla Reddy Garu in 1997. The college is affiliated with the Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University, Hyderabad and is approved by AICTE. Further, the institute is accredited by NAAC & NBA (AICTE) and ISO 9001:2015 Certified Institution.

Ghousia College of Engineering (GCE), Ramanagar, established in 1980, is approved by AICTE, NBA and Govt. of Karnataka and affiliated to Visvesvaraya Technical University, Belgaum. It offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses in the discipline of Engineering and Science. Admission to GCE depends on the performance of the candidates in the state level entrance examination.

College Name: Global Institute of Engineering and Technology - [GIT]
Info Data: Global Institute of Engineering and Technology (GIET), established in 2009, is a private institute affiliated to Anna University and approved by AICTE. The institute offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses in the discipline of Engineering. Admission in the GIET is done on the basis of the TNEA entrance exam. The institute has a dedicated Training and Placement Cell who provides 100% placement assistance to its students. More than 91% of students get placed through the campus placement every year.

College Name: Gopalan College of Engineering and Management - [GCEM]
Info Data: Gopalan College of Engineering and Management (GCEM) were started by the Gopalan Foundation, which is part of the renowned Gopalan Group. The Gopalan Group was founded in 1984 by Mr. C.Gopalan, an architect, with the objective of developing and constructing residential apartments in Bangalore.

Green Hills Engineering College (GHEC), Solan is managed by a trust   constituting of members who are education oriented. Members of the GHEC Society are always willing to propagate knowledge through discipline and spread the light of education.

Hasmukh Goswami College of Engineering (HGCE), Ahmedabad was established by Shree Monark Education Trust in the year 2000. Hasmukh Goswami College offers B.E, M.E, MBA and Diploma in various streams. Admission to the HGCE is done as per the guidelines of ACPC or Management Quota. In the year 2020, a total of 21 companies visited for on-campus recruitment and 27 students got placed. The highest package is recorded at INR 3,36,875 and the average package is recorded at INR 2,00,000. Some of the potential employers include Axis Bank, Squad technologies, GTPL broadband, Etech, IMS, Karnavati Engineering Ltd, EclinicalWorks, Darkhorse Analytics, etc

Hindusthan Institute of Technology (HITECH), Coimbatore offers B.E./B.Tech at UG level and M.E/M.Tech and MBA at PG level. The fees for B.Tech program is INR 5 Lacs, whereas HITECH fees for the MBA program is INR 90,000. Admissions to B.Tech are based on merit basis, while for M.Tech/M.E is based on the entrance exams TANCET / CET / GATE.  The admission for MBA takes place through entrance exams MAT / TANCET / CET.

Institute of Engineering and Technology, Alwar was established in the year 1998. IET is promoted by All India Society for Advance Education and Research. College is Rajasthan Technical University, Kota and is approved by AICTE.

College Name: KG Reddy College of Engineering and Technology - [KGRCET]
Info Data: KG Reddy College of Engineering and Technology (KGRCET), Hyderabad has been granted Autonomous Status by UGC and ‘A+’ Grade by NAAC. KG Reddy College of Engineering and Technology is awarded “Best Upcoming Engineering College” by Times CyberMedia and ranked among “Top 25 Private Engineering Colleges” in Telangana by Times of India for the last 3 years. It is ranked amongst the top 16 Private Engineering colleges in Telangana and ranked #9 amongst top 10 Telangana Private institutes for placements. KGRCET has received 3.5 Star rating by Institute Innovation Council (IIC) and ARIIA Brand B performance category. KGRCET has received NBA accreditation for CSE and ECE branches.

K.L.N College of Information Technology (KLNCIT), Pottapalayam was established in 2001. The college has dedicated faculty members having vast academic, research, consultancy and industrial experience. Besides imparting quality technical education in classrooms, the teachers and their supporting staff in different laboratories, drawing halls and computer labs make the learning atmosphere conducive, inspiring and enjoyable.

KNS Institute of Technology, located in Bangalore, is one of the prestigious engineering institutes in the country. The college is affiliated with Visvesvaraya Technological University and is approved by AICTE. It has also got recognition from Govt. of Karnataka. The college campus is spread over 20 acres of land in Bangalore City. KNSIT was inaugurated by Mrs. Sonia Gandhi in the presence of Shri S. M. Krishna, Former C.M. of Karnataka. The institute offers 5 undergraduate courses under its BE degree. Admission is granted based on the candidate’s score in the qualifying KCET Exam.

College Name: KCC Institute of Technology and Management - [KCCITM]
Info Data: KCC Institute of Technology and Management is located in Greater Noida, Uttar Pradesh. It is one of the sister institutes for engineering and management studies under KCC institutions. It has approvals from the All India Council of Technical Education (AICTE) and UGC and affiliation from Dr APJ Abdul Kalam Technical University (AKTU).

Lakhmi Chand Institute of Technology (LCIT), Bilaspur established in 2008, under the aegis of Shree ShreeVidyaSagarjiMaharaj, is a name synonymous with holistic education; the institute has single mindedly pursued commitment to provide the youth the opportunity to receive high quality education of global standards. The College is affiliated to Chhatisgarh Swami Vivekananda Technical university and approved by AICTE

College Name: Lendi Institute of Engineering and Technology
Info Data: Lendi Institute of Engineering and Technology was established in the year 2008 under the aegis ofSai Dhamam Educational Trust, Visakhapatnam. The college is affiliated to Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University, Kakinada and approved by AICTE. It offers UG and PG courses in Engineering

MAM College of Engineering (MAMCE), Trichy offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses in various fields of Engineering such as Electronics & Communication Engineering, Electrical & Electronics Engineering, and Mechanical Engineering. It also offers a Master's course in Management and Computer Applications. Admission to UG and PG courses is based on several entrance exams conducted at national and state levels.

College Name: Marri Laxman Reddy Institute of Technology & Management - [MLRITM]
Info Data: MLRITM was established by a group of intellectuals, eminent professionals and industrialists in the year 2009. MLRITM falls under the aegis of Marri Laxman Reddy Group of Institutions. The college is approved by AICTE, New Delhi. The college offers B.Tech, MBA and M.Tech courses in diverse disciplines at the undergraduate and the postgraduate level. Admission to the B.Tech is based on valid scores in TS-EAMCET and for MBA admission is based on TSICET. The institute has associations and MOUs with a lot of industries in various fields for imparting training to students at a professional level, some of them include IBM, Microsoft etc.

The Maharaja Institute of Technology is an institute under Maharaja Education Trust in the field of science and engineering technology. The College is equipped with all modern learning aids to make teaching-learning process a pleasure. The highly qualified staff is its asset. The college has to its credit the highest number of admissions in the academic year 2007-08 among the 16 newly opened engineering colleges in Karnataka.

Maharana Pratap Engineering College, a private engineering college in Kanpur, was established in 1999 by the Maharana Pratap Group of Institutions. The College campus is spread over 50 acres of land located near Mandhana on G.T. Road, 3 km from IIT, Kanpur. It aims to prepare the students to walk on the untrodden pathway with devoted discipline and internal enthusiasm to take victory in their stride. It offers under graduate and post graduate courses in various disciplines.

College Name: Malla Reddy College of Engineering and Technology- [MRCET]
Info Data: Malla Reddy College of Engineering and Technology (MRCET) Hyderabad, is a public (autonomous) institution, established in 2004, approved by AICTE and UGC u/s 2(f) and 12(B) of the UGC Act, affiliated to Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University Hyderabad. The institution in NAAC accredited ‘A’ Grade. The institute provides undergraduate and postgraduate programs in Engineering and Management.

Malla Reddy Institute of Technology (MRIT) Secunderabad, is a private institution, established in 2008, approved by AICTE, affiliated to Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University Hyderabad, located in the Secunderabad, Telangana. MRIT is a perfect combination of industrial expertise & well-qualified faculties with a grooming environment for the students to develop their skills. The institution offers undergraduate and postgraduate Engineering programs.

Mallabhum Institute of Technology (MIT), Bankura was established in 2002. Task of the MIT is not only to maintain its leading position, but also to move forward. MIT can attribute its success to two inherent advantages it has, students and faculty members coming from different parts of India is providing a cross cultural learning environment, which is an abundance of natural surroundings, fosters an ideal achieving climate.

College Name: Malwa Institute of Science and Technology - [MIST]
Info Data: Malwa Institute of Science and Technology (MIST Indore) is an engineering institute offering Undergraduate, Postgraduate, and Diploma courses in various specializations of engineering. The selection of students in these courses is made on the basis of marks obtained in the qualifying entrance examinations. The accepted exam scores at MIST Indore are JEE Main and GATE.

Mewat Engineering College is the pioneer college in the field of Engineering in India. With the vision to provide excellence in technical education, meet the growing demands of industries in the future and benefit the society as a whole. It is a full fledged college imparting full time programme B.Tech in Computer Science & Engineering, Electrical and Electronics Engineering, Electronics and Communications Engineering, Mechanical Engineering and Civil Engineering.The College aims at providing modern education alongside Islamic education to the minority community. In addition to running various schools, vocational institutions, providing grants to number of schools and colleges; the Board has established Mewat Engineering College (Waqf).

P.B. College of Engineering (PBCE), Irungkattukottai was established in 2002. The institute is managed by P.B Educational Trust. It is a Telugu Minority Institution. College strives to achieve global identity through its innovative methods and strenuous efforts for the betterment of the student’s community. The college is committed to provide quality education to the students enabling them to excel in the fields of engineering, science, technology and management to cater to the changing and challenging needs of society and industry.

College Name: Progressive Education Society's Modern College of Engineering - [MCOE]
Info Data: PES Modern College of Engineering (PESMCOE), Pune was established in 1999. Modern College of Engineering is an institute of higher education offering quality programs that integrate professional skills and career focused education empowering students to develop and achieve their personal and career potentials

Raghu Institute of Technology strives to equip the students with required conceptual, technical and managerial skills to meet the present and future requirements of the industry. The main aim of the institute is to train qualified professional in the field of engineering to cater the technology needs of the society and to shoulder the ever-changing business responsibilities at national and international levels.

College Name: Rajiv Gandhi College of Engineering and Technology
Info Data: Rajiv Gandhi College of Engineering and Technology is sponsored by Sri Balaji Educational and Charitable Public Trust. It is located in a beautiful, scenic location in an area of 30 acres at Kirumambakkam. The campus is well connected by road and rail service. The college has got its approval from AICTE for its various courses. Pondicherry University has provided affiliation to the college.

College Name: Reva Institute of Technology and Management - [RITM]
Info Data: Reva Institute of Technology and Management (RITM), Bangalore pursues the path of holistic education where the student community is the main point of the learning process. Motto of the RITM is knowledge is power. This is meaningfully complemented by the parent community and teaching community working together towards a common goal of excellence.

SKP Engineering College (SKPEC) is one of the prestigious Engineering colleges in Tamil Nadu. It was established in 1999 and aims at providing quality education to students belonging to rural backgrounds in and around Tiruvannamalai. SKPEC’s goal is to impart technical education and skills to students so that they become better professionals in the industry and even go for higher education equipped with confidence.

Scient Institute of Technology Ibrahimpatnam, is a private college, located in Hyderabad, Telangana. It was established in 2001. It is approved by All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE) and affiliated to JNTU. It offers B. Tech, M. Tech, and MBA courses. The student admissions are based on the rank obtained in EAMCET / ICET entrance tests for B.Tech and MBA respectively. The Student admissions are based on the rank obtained in GATE / PG-ECET entrance tests for M.Tech. The student admissions are governed by the rules and regulations of the Telangana State Council of Higher Education (TSCHE).

College Name: Shree Swami Atmanand Saraswati Institute of Technology - [SSASIT]
Info Data: Shree Swami Atmanand Saraswati Institute of Technology (SSASIT) Surat is an engineering college established in May 2009. The institute is a part of Shree Tapi Brahmcharyashram Sabha Trust. All the courses at SSASIT Surat are approved by AICTE, New Delhi. It is affiliated to Gujarat Technological University, Ahmedabad. The college holds various co-curricular activities throughout the year.

College Name: St Xaviers Catholic College of Engineering - [SXCCE]
Info Data: St. Xavier Catholic College of Engineering is a private college owned by Roman Catholic Diocese of Kuzhithurai. It is located in Chunkankadai, Kanyakumari District, Nagercoil, Tamil Nadu. The college is affiliated to Anna University, Chennai. It is AICTE and UGC approved college. MBA Program provided in the college has permanent affiliation from the Anna University.

Surya Engineering College (SEC), Erode was established in 2008 under the auspices of Sri Andavar Educational and Charitable Trust. Aim of the college is to impart engineering and management education of high standards, ensure customer satisfaction and to become an institute of repute through continual improvement.

T John Institute of Technology is a private engineering college established in the year 2006 with aim to produce quality engineers. It is part of T John Group of institutions. Institute’s vision is to be recognized as among top engineering institutes of the country.

The Technocrats institute of Technology is a part of one of the premier institutes in Central India i.e., Technocrats TIT Group. The college offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses in six disciplines each for Engineering and Management. And the admission into these courses is done via entrance exams i.e., JEE MAIN/ GATE after which the student is admitted on the basis of the counseling done by DTE. At the end of the course, the college offers 100% placement opportunities to its students among the prominent companies in the market like Facebook, Netflix, SAP, etc. The college was recently awarded as the “Best Institute of Engineering in Central India - 2019” by the HRD Ministry, Govt. of India.

Teegala Krishna Reddy Engineering College, Hyderabad established in 2002, is affiliated to JNTUH, Hyderabad and is approved by AICTE. The college offers various UG, PG and Diploma courses in Engineering & Technology and Management. Admission in the college is done on the basis of the performance of the candidates in the state and national level entrance exams. In 2020, the cutoff for B.Tech Computer Science Engineering was 60576 for male candidates and 75919 for female candidates.

College Name: Toc H Institute of Science and Technology - [TIST]
Info Data: Toc H Institute of Science and Technology was established in 2002 and is affiliated to APJ Abdul Kalam Technological University (AKTU) and approved by the All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE) and the Government of Kerala. TIST offers a B.Tech program at the UG level, M. Tech, and MBA at the PG level along with the PhD program at the Doctoral level. Admission to B.Tech and M.Tech programs is granted based on KEAM and GATE scores, respectively. Admission to the MBA program is offered based on KMAT/CAT/CMATE score. Institute offers 100% placement assistance to students and scholarships to eligible students on the basis of merit, entrance exam scores, family income, etc.

Walchand Institute of Technology (WIT), established in 1983, is the oldest engineering college in Solapur, India. WIT is managed by Shri Aillak Pannalal Digambar Jain Pathashala Trust and is named after Seth Walchand Hirachand, one of India's pioneers of industrial development.

College Name: Truba College of Science and Technology - [TCST]
Info Data: Truba Institute of Science and Technology, Bhopal is a private co-educational engineering college. College offers 5 undergraduate engineering courses. College is affiliated to Rajiv Gandhi Technical University and is AICTE approved.

Jain College of Engineering (JCE), Belgaum was established in 2010. The college is approved by AICTE and affiliated to Visvesvaraya Technological University. The college has been managed by Jain Group of Institutions, a dynamic and forward looking institution, committed to excellence in teaching, learning, enterprise and research. The aim of JCE is to provide the highest quality of educational experience for students from every walk of life.

College Name: M.A.M. College of Engineering and Technology - [MAMCET]
Info Data: MAM College of Engineering and Technology (MAMCET) was established in 2008 by M.A.M. Group of Institutions with the aim of providing quality education on par with international standards. It is situated in a very serene atmosphere free from all kinds of pollutions. It is located at Trichy-Chennai Trunk Road Siruganur, Trichy. The college is affiliated to Anna University, offers undergraduate, postgraduate in the field of engineering, technology, and management programs such as B.Tech, M.E., MBA, and other programs. Admission to such courses is done on the basis of several entrance exams conducted at national and state levels.

College Name: Velammal College of Engineering and Technology - [VCET]
Info Data: Velammal College of Engineering and Technology (VCET) was established 2007 and it is affiliated to Anna University, Chennai. It is a self-financing non-minority institution. It is founded by Shri. M. V. Muthuramalingam, a Professional Engineer and the Chairman of the Velammal Educational Trust, Chennai. The College has excelled at providing a high-quality, affordable education to students of diverse backgrounds, many of them children of immigrants, working-class students and others seeking access to an outstanding private institution. The College campus is classical, high-style buildings to be constructed on 26 acres. The College is approved by NAAC.

College Name: Vignan Institute of Technology And Management
Info Data: Vignan Institute of Technology and Management was developed by the Vignan Educational Trust in the year 2008, order to produce world-class technocrats.  College is located near famous Sidha Temple, 17 km from Berhampur Town.

College Name: Mangalmay Institute of Engineering and Technology - [MIET]
Info Data: Mangalmay Institute of Engineering and Technology (MIET), Greater Noida is ranked 15th for Engineering by Amar Ujala & IMRB International Education Survey and ranked AAA by Business & Management Chronicle. MIET Noida assures placement opportunities to students. More than 200 companies have visited for on-campus placement. MIET offers a degree course in the discipline of Engineering.

United Institute of Technology has been established with the sole objective to cater the demand of high quality technical education in the region of Tamil Nadu to make the new generation excellent in technology and research activities.

College Name: Vidya Academy of Science and Technology - [VAST]
Info Data: Vidya Academy of Science and Technology in Kerala is approved by the AICTE. The institute is affiliated with APJ Abdul Kalam Technological University. It is part of the Vidya International Charitable Trust.

College Name: Viswajyothi College of Engineering and Technology - [VJCET]
Info Data: Viswajyothi College of Engineering and Technology (VCET) was established in 2001. It is a private engineering college, run by the Syro-Malabar Catholic diocese of Kothamangalam. This institute is affiliated with Mahatma Gandhi University. VCET offers B.Tech.  course in Civil, Mechanical, Computer science and Electrical and Electronic Engineering. This institute also offers MBA, and M.Tech courses which are approved by AICTE. College has highly committed Management Team and technocrats faculty members.

The ICFAI Foundation for Higher Education is a Deemed-to-be-University established in the year 2008. IFHE campus is a 92-acre lush green sylvan campus with a built-up area of over 16 lakh sq. ft. ICFAI University Hyderabad Admissions offers many UG, PG, Ph.D & Certificate level courses such as B.Tech, BBA, BBA-LLB, BA-LLB, MBA, M.Tech, LLM, PhD(Full time/Part time). Programs under many departments are offered via IBS Hyderabad (Faculty of Management), Faculty of Science and Technology (FST), Faculty of Law (ICFAI Law School Hyderabad), ICFAI School of Architecture. Application forms for admission can be filled online by visiting the University website. It acquired 40th NIRF rank this year in the management category.

The Institute of Chartered Financial Analysts of India (ICFAI) University, Raipur imparts career-oriented educational programs at UG, PG, Diploma & PG Diploma levels. There are 15 programs offered in multiple disciplines in management, information technology, and science & technology. Check ICFAI University Raipur Courses & Fees

Alakh Prakash Goyal Shimla University (APG Shimla) has been awarded as Asia’s Greatest Brand and the Most Promising University in the year 2019 and 2017 respectively. It offers various undergraduate and postgraduate courses in the fields of Engineering, Arts, Journalism and Mass Communication such as B.Tech, BJMC, M.Tech, MJMC, Ph.D., etc. The admission of such programs is based on merit in past academics and several entrance exams. The University also conducts its own entrance test, AIECST. AP Goyal Shimla University has a record of providing 100% placement assistance and provides training and internship from the first semester. The highest package is recorded at INR 32 LPA and the average package is INR 3.6 LPA. More than 5000 students have been placed in their on-campus recruitment.

Mohammad Ali Jauhar University is a private university established under University Act in the year 2006. University offers courses in Life Science, humanities, science, law, mass communication, engineering, agriculture, and technology.  University aims to provide multidisciplinary research and education on the level of excellence. University has facilities for various games like chess, badminton, table tennis, hockey, cricket, etc. The University System looks for creative and successful answers for its difficulties and creates ways to satisfy its mission.  University visions To make a friendly scholastic environment for attaining to magnificence, advancing creative considering, creating inventive bowed of the brain and instilling human qualities and to give the cutting edge and established training to Muslims specifically.

PCTE group of institutes was the first institute established by the Punjab Management Education Trust at Ludhiana, with the motive of providing good management and IT education in the region. The college recognizes that the dynamic business landscape would require young business leaders who not only have an understanding of the developing economies but also present a global perspective. Pursuits of academic excellence and fostering total person integral growth, intellectual, emotional, spiritual, and social persona of students have been the hallmark of PCTE over the years.

Dayananda Sagar Institutions (DSI), Bangalore is run under the aegis of the Mahatma Gandhi Vidya Peetha Trust, in Bangalore described as the Silicon Valley of India. Stress is laid not only on the quality of education, but also on the quality of life in our many campuses, to over-see the total transformation and development of students covered under the DSI banner

Bangalore Technological Institute (BTI), Bangalore is a part of the Aditya Educational Trust and with a prime motive to produce skillful professionals to the industry the Bangalore Technological Institution is dedicated in offering an outstanding academic schedule. Along with the curricular programs the institution is organizing various training sessions which will boost the self confidence of the students and enhances their soft skills. The management even conducts sports and cultural meets as they believe that overall development helps an individual to be successful.

College Name: A. C. Patil College of Engineering - [ACPCE]
Info Data: Today, Jawahar Education Society’s A. C. Patil College of Engineering (ACPCE) is a premium Technical Institute offering graduate and postgraduate professional Degrees in Engineering and Management and is approved by apex technical bodies, All India Council for Technical Education New Delhi (AICTE), recognized by Director of Technical Education Maharashtra State (DTE) and is affiliated to Mumbai University since last 25 years.

College Name: Vasantdada Patil Pratishtan's College of Engineering & Visual Arts
Info Data: Vasantdada Patil Pratishtan's College of Engineering & Visual Arts is ranked 2nd among the Mumbai Colleges by Higher Education Review and ranked 9th in the "Top 20 Engineering Colleges in India with Excellent Industry Exposure" in 2017. The institute is approved by All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE), New Delhi and Directorate of Technical Education (DTE), Maharashtra and affiliated to University of Mumbai to conduct degree courses in Computer Engineering, Electronics and Telecommunication Engineering and Information Technology.

PPG Institute of Technology (PPGIT), a college under the power of P. Perichi Gounder Memorial Education and Charitable Trust (PPG Trust), Coimbatore was established in the year 2008. The college was founded by Dr. L.P. Thangavelu, who is chairman of the college presently.The college’s motive is to provide highly qualified, eminent, committed and dedicated faculty with vast knowledge and experience who take personal interest in the development and moulding of each student. Vadodara Institute of Engineering (VIE), Vadodara is ranked 5th out of 114 GTU Affiliated Colleges and ranked 1st consistently out of 9 colleges in the Vadodara region for the last 4 years. College Name: JD College of Engineering and Management
Info Data: JD College of Engineering and Management, shortly referred to as JDCOEM, was established in 2008 as a private autonomous institute in Nagpur. It offers multiple specializations under B.Tech, M.Tech, MBA, and Ph.D. courses. Admissions to these courses are on the basis of various entrance examinations such as JEE Main, MH CET, GATE, etc. Applications are accepted online. The college has a placement rate of 78.46%, with Amazon and HCL among its top recruiters. It also provides scholarships.

College Name: Shree L. R. Tiwari College of Engineering - [SLRTCE]

Within the first year of its inception, the college had already become one of the most preferable engineering colleges in the extended western suburbs of Mumbai. Shree L. R. Tiwari College of Engineering Admissions is done as per the norms/guidelines of Maharashtra Unaided Private Professional Institutions. The college offers Bachelor of Engineering and Master of Engineering in various specializations.

Apex Professional University APU is a non-profit, private university, established in 2013, by the Government of Arunachal Pradesh and Apex Foundation, Bangalore, located at the Pasighat in Distt. East Siang, Arunachal Pradesh. The University offers various courses at UG, PG & PhD levels.

Haridwar University, Roorkee formerly known as Roorkee College of Engineering is awarded the “Best Upcoming Engineering College in Uttarakhand Award” under CMAI National Uttarakhand Award Jointly by CMAI, AICTE, UTU and awarded the “Best Technical Institute in Uttarakhand Award” by CMAI, AICTE, and MTU. Haridwar University offers undergraduate, postgraduate and diploma programs in the discipline of Engineering, Pharmacy, Management, Tourism Management, etc.

Providence College of Engineering and School of Business (PCESB), Chengannur was established in 2015, is affiliated with AKTU and approved by AICTE. Additionally, more than 80%-90% eligible students got placed from the 2015-19 batch across multiple companies. The highest package is offered at INR 3.2 LPA and the average package is offered at INR 2 LPA. Some of the top recruiters are IBM, UST Global TCS, Stanadyne, Habitat, Capgemini, etc.

Dr. N.G.P. Institute of Technology (NGPIT) is one of the institutes run by KMCH & Dr. NGP Educational trust. Graduates from the institute are placed in well-reputed companies such as IBM, HDFC Bank, HCL, FSS, ZIFO, Cognizant, Amazon, Aspire Systems, etc. The average salary package received by the students stands at INR 3 LPA and the highest package reaches up to INR 10 LPA. NGPIT offers UG, PG, and Doctoral programs in the fields of Engineering and Management. Admission to the institute is entrance-based. The accepted exam scores are TANCET and GATE.

Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan University Bhopal, is a private university, established by RKDF Group, recognized by MP Private Universities Regulatory Commission under section MP Act No: 17 of 2007 & covered U/S 2 (f) of UGC Act in 2015, located in the Bhopal city of Madhya Pradesh. H.V. P Mandal’s College of Engineering and Technology (HVPM-COET) was established in 2002 in Amravati, Maharashtra. It is approved by AICTE and DTE. Candidates can apply to the college in online mode.

Info Data: Adani Institute of Infrastructure Engineering (AIIE) was founded in the year 2015. IAMR has 5 institutes and 1 school in Ghaziabad and Meerut.

Amritsar Group of Colleges (AGC), Amritsar has become a pioneer of world-class education for the last 16 years. AGC offers degree courses in the discipline of Engineering & Technology, Law and Pharmacy. Admission to various UG and PG courses is done on the basis of AGC NEST conducted by the institute. AGC has placed more than 4567 students in its on-campus placement. The highest package is recorded at INR 40 LPA and the average package ranges from INR 10-12 LPA. Some of the potential employers of AGC are TCS, Infosys, Cognizant, Accenture, Amazon, iGate, Tech Mahindra, AON, Luminous, IBM, Ericsson, LG Soft, Indus Tower, ITC, GVK, Daikin Air Conditioning, Polaris, Appirio, Sopra Steria, HCL, NagarroEscorts, Eicher, Michigan Tyres, etc. The AGC campus is spread over more than 16 acres of land and has many colleges which offer a wide range of courses. Gokul Global University has various colleges for various courses like Hansaba college of engineering and technology, Gokul Nursing College, Gokul Science College, and also has various on-campus facilities for the students. The university is recognized by the UGC, Bar Council of India, AICTE. The admission to the UG level program is based on 10+2.

The college offers various UG, PG and Diploma courses in the discipline of Engineering, Technology, Management and Computer Application. The flagship courses of the college are B.Tech across 8 specializations, M.Tech in 5 specializations and MBA across 5 specializations. Apart from that, WCTM also offers BBA, BCA, MCA and Polytechnic Diploma courses. Admission to the B.Tech program is done on the basis of the  scores. Candidates seeking admission in the M.Tech course, candidates ne4ed to obtain a valid score in GATE. The college accepts , MAT, , XAT entrance exam scores for MBA admission. However, the selection of candidates for the other courses is merit-based.

College Name: Adhi College of Engineering and Technology - [ACET]
Info Data: Adhi College of Engineering and Technology was established in the year 2008-2009, with the Approval of Government of Tamil Nadu and AICTE, New Delhi.

Adichunchanagiri Institute of Technology (AIT), Chikmagalur was established in 1980 under Adhichunchanagiri Shikshana Trust. The institute is affiliated with Visvesvaraya Technological University, Belgaum. It is recognized by the All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE), New Delhi, and accredited by the National Board of Accreditation (NBA), New Delhi. It is an ISO 9001:2008 certified institute. The objective of the institute is committed to quality education, training & research providing quality technical education, and molding the younger generation with the spirit of service to society. The institute is located in the famous Chickmagalur city which is 240 km from Bangalore, the capital of Karnataka, and well connected by bus routes to all the major cities and towns of the state. The nearest railway station is at Kadur (or Birur) on the Bangalore - Bombay broad gauge line, which is 35 km away.

The main objective of an institute is to generate a bunch of highly creative professionals, who can contribute not only in the human resource development but also in the nation building exercise. The mission of the college is to prepare students for higher level of education in engineering, technology and sciences so that they become competent, creative and imaginative professionals.

Allenhouse Institute of Technology, Kanpur is a private engineering institute, affiliated to AKTU Lucknow. Established in 2009 under Superhouse Group, it is approved by the AICTE, New Delhi. Anjalai Ammal-Mahalingam Engineering College (AAMEC), Kovilvenni was established in the year 1995 under the self financing scheme by the Mazdoor Welfare Trust. CSI College of Engineering, Nilgiris is committed towards providing quality education to the students helping them to excel in every field. It endeavors to cater to the changing needs and challenging demands of the industry and society. It emphasize on the attaining academic excellence by providing the proper infrastructure and a congenial environment for learning. It helps in collaboration with the industries and promotes research and development.   It targets at continuous improvement in technical education through the Quality Management Systems. It works on the principle which considers action to be the ultimate aim of education instead of knowledge. It strives to equip the students with the technical knowledge; aims at inculcating right attitude in them; motivates them to take independent decision; so that they can be useful human resource for shouldering the responsibility of the industry.

Geeta Engineering College (GEC), Panipat was established by the Geeta Group of Institutions, run by K.R. Education Society. Its main objective is to promote developments of residents of Rural India by dealing with issues like health, literacy etc.

Info Institute of Engineering (IIE) is a private engineering educational Institute, located in Kovilpalayam, Coimbatore, Tamil Nadu, India.. The college was established in 2007. However, a candidate’s performance in 10+2 examinations is also taken into consideration for the same.

It offers eight under graduate and four post graduate courses.

College Name: LDRP Institute of Technology and Research - [LDRPITR]
